quran[669]{c,v,t}:
  1,1,"In the Name of Allah‚ÄĒthe Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  1,2,All praise is for Allah‚ÄĒLord of all worlds
  1,3,"the Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  1,4,Master of the Day of Judgment
  1,5,You ňĻaloneňļ we worship and You ňĻaloneňļ we ask for help
  1,6,Guide us along the Straight Path
  1,7,"the Path of those You have blessed‚ÄĒnot those You are displeased with, or those who are astray"
  2,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m
  2,2,This is the Book! There is no doubt about it‚ÄĒa guide for those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ
  2,3,"who believe in the unseen,¬†establish prayer, and donate from what We have provided for them"
  2,4,"and who believe in what has been revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ¬†and what was revealed before you, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  2,5,"It is they who are ňĻtrulyňļ guided by their Lord, and it is they who will be successful"
  2,6,"As for those who persist in disbelief, it is the same whether you warn them or not‚ÄĒthey will never believe"
  2,7,"Allah has sealed their hearts and their hearing, and their sight is covered. They will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  2,8,"And there are some who say, ‚ÄúWe believe in Allah and the Last Day,‚ÄĚ yet they are not ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  2,9,"They seek to deceive Allah and the believers, yet they only deceive themselves, but they fail to perceive it"
  2,10,"There is sickness in their hearts, and Allah ňĻonlyňļ lets their sickness increase. They will suffer a painful punishment for their lies"
  2,11,"When they are told, ‚ÄúDo not spread corruption in the land,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúWe are only peace-makers!‚ÄĚ"
  2,12,"Indeed, it is they who are the corruptors, but they fail to perceive it"
  2,13,"And when they are told, ‚ÄúBelieve as others believe,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúWill we believe as the fools believe?‚ÄĚ Indeed, it is they who are fools, but they do not know"
  2,14,"When they meet the believers they say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ But when alone with their evil associates they say, ‚ÄúWe are definitely with you; we were only mocking.‚ÄĚ"
  2,15,"Allah will throw their mockery back at them, leaving them to continue wandering blindly in their defiance"
  2,16,"They are the ones who trade guidance for misguidance. But this trade is profitless, and they are not ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  2,17,"Their example is that of someone who kindles a fire, but when it lights up all around them, Allah takes away their light, leaving them in complete darkness‚ÄĒunable to see"
  2,18,"They are ňĻwilfullyňļ deaf, dumb, and blind, so they will never return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  2,19,"Or ňĻthose caught inňļ a rainstorm from the sky with darkness, thunder, and lightning. They press their fingers into their ears at the sound of every thunder-clap for fear of death. And Allah encompasses the disbelievers ňĻby His mightňļ"
  2,20,"It is as if the lightning were about to snatch away their sight. Whenever lightning strikes, they walk in its light, but when darkness covers them, they stand still. Had Allah willed, He could have taken away their hearing and sight. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,21,"O humanity! Worship your Lord, Who created you and those before you, so that you may become mindful ňĻof Himňļ"
  2,22,"ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who has made the earth a place of settlement for you and the sky a canopy; and sends down rain from the sky, causing fruits to grow as a provision for you. So do not knowingly set up equals to Allah ňĻin worshipňļ"
  2,23,"And if you are in doubt about what We have revealed to Our servant,¬†then produce a s√Ľrah¬†like it and call your helpers other than Allah, if what you say is true"
  2,24,"But if you are unable to do so‚ÄĒand you will never be able to do so‚ÄĒthen fear the Fire fuelled with people and stones, which is prepared for the disbelievers"
  2,25,"Give good news ňĻO Prophetňļ to those who believe and do good that they will have Gardens under which rivers flow. Whenever provided with fruit, they will say, ‚ÄúThis is what we were given before,‚ÄĚ for they will be served fruit that looks similar ňĻbut tastes differentňļ. They will have pure spouses,¬†and they will be there forever"
  2,26,"Surely Allah does not shy away from using the parable of a mosquito or what is even smaller. As for the believers, they know that it is the truth from their Lord. And as for the disbelievers, they argue, ‚ÄúWhat does Allah mean by such a parable?‚ÄĚ Through this ňĻtestňļ, He leaves many to stray, and guides many. And He leaves none to stray except the rebellious‚ÄĒ"
  2,27,"those who violate Allah‚Äôs covenant after it has been affirmed, break whatever ňĻtiesňļ Allah has ordered to be maintained, and spread corruption in the land. It is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ losers"
  2,28,"How can you deny Allah? You were lifeless and He gave you life, then He will cause you to die and again bring you to life, and then to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  2,29,"He is the One Who created everything in the earth for you. Then He turned towards the heaven, forming it into seven heavens. And He has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  2,30,"ňĻRememberňļ when your Lord said to the angels, ‚ÄúI am going to place a successive ňĻhumanňļ authority on earth.‚ÄĚ They asked ňĻAllahňļ, ‚ÄúWill You place in it someone who will spread corruption there and shed blood while we glorify Your praises and proclaim Your holiness?‚ÄĚ Allah responded, ‚ÄúI know what you do not know.‚ÄĚ"
  2,31,"He taught Adam the names of all things, then He presented them to the angels and said, ‚ÄúTell Me the names of these, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  2,32,"They replied, ‚ÄúGlory be to You! We have no knowledge except what You have taught us. You are truly the All-Knowing, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  2,33,"Allah said, ‚ÄúO Adam! Inform them of their names.‚ÄĚ Then when Adam did, Allah said, ‚ÄúDid I not tell you that I know the secrets of the heavens and the earth, and I know what you reveal and what you conceal?‚ÄĚ"
  2,34,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We said to the angels, ‚ÄúProstrate before Adam,‚ÄĚ¬†so they all did‚ÄĒbut not Ibl√ģs,¬†who refused and acted arrogantly,¬†becoming unfaithful"
  2,35,"We cautioned, ‚ÄúO Adam! Live with your wife in Paradise and eat as freely as you please, but do not approach this tree, or else you will be wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,36,"But Satan deceived them‚ÄĒleading to their fall from the ňĻblissfulňļ state they were in,¬†and We said, ‚ÄúDescend from the heavens ňĻto the earthňļ as enemies to each other.¬†You will find in the earth a residence and provision for your appointed stay.‚ÄĚ"
  2,37,"Then Adam was inspired with words ňĻof prayerňļ by his Lord,¬†so He accepted his repentance. Surely He is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,38,"We said, ‚ÄúDescend all of you! Then when guidance comes to you from Me, whoever follows it, there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,39,But those who disbelieve and deny Our signs will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever.‚ÄĚ
  2,40,"O children of Israel!¬†Remember My favours upon you. Fulfil your covenant and I will fulfil Mine, and stand in awe of Me ňĻaloneňļ"
  2,41,Believe in My revelations which confirm your Scriptures.¬†Do not be the first to deny them or trade them for a fleeting gain.¬†And be mindful of Me
  2,42,Do not mix truth with falsehood or hide the truth knowingly
  2,43,"Establish prayer, pay alms-tax,¬†and bow down with those who bow down"
  2,44,"Do you preach righteousness and fail to practice it yourselves, although you read the Scripture? Do you not understand"
  2,45,"And seek help through patience and prayer. Indeed, it is a burden except for the humble‚ÄĒ"
  2,46,those who are certain that they will meet their Lord and to Him they will return
  2,47,O Children of Israel! Remember ňĻallňļ the favours I granted you and how I honoured you above the others
  2,48,"Guard yourselves against the Day on which no soul will be of help to another. No intercession¬†will be accepted, no ransom taken, and no help will be given"
  2,49,"ňĻRememberňļ how We delivered you from the people of Pharaoh, who afflicted you with dreadful torment, slaughtering your sons and keeping your women. That was a severe test from your Lord"
  2,50,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We parted the sea, rescued you, and drowned Pharaoh‚Äôs people before your very eyes"
  2,51,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We appointed forty nights for Moses, then you worshipped the calf in his absence, acting wrongfully"
  2,52,Even then We ňĻstillňļ forgave you so perhaps you would be grateful
  2,53,And ňĻrememberňļ when We gave Moses the Scripture‚ÄĒthe standard ňĻto distinguish between right and wrongňļ that perhaps you would be ňĻrightlyňļ guided
  2,54,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Moses said to his people, ‚ÄúO my people! Surely you have wronged yourselves by worshipping the calf, so turn in repentance to your Creator and execute ňĻthe calf-worshippers amongňļ yourselves. That is best for you in the sight of your Creator.‚ÄĚ Then He accepted your repentance. Surely He is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,55,"And ňĻrememberňļ when you said, ‚ÄúO Moses! We will never believe you until we see Allah with our own eyes,‚ÄĚ so a thunderbolt struck you while you were looking on"
  2,56,"Then We brought you back to life after your death, so that perhaps you would be grateful"
  2,57,"And ňĻremember whenňļ We shaded you with clouds and sent down to you manna and quails,¬†ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúEat from the good things We have provided for you.‚ÄĚ The evildoers ňĻcertainlyňļ did not wrong Us, but wronged themselves"
  2,58,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We said, ‚ÄúEnter this city and eat freely from wherever you please; enter the gate with humility, saying, ‚ÄėAbsolve us.‚Äô We will forgive your sins and multiply the reward for the good-doers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,59,But the wrongdoers changed the words they were commanded to say. So We sent down a punishment from the heavens upon them for their rebelliousness
  2,60,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Moses prayed for water for his people, We said, ‚ÄúStrike the rock with your staff.‚ÄĚ Then twelve springs gushed out, ňĻandňļ each tribe knew its drinking place. ňĻWe then said,ňļ ‚ÄúEat and drink of Allah‚Äôs provisions, and do not go about spreading corruption in the land.‚ÄĚ"
  2,61,"And ňĻrememberňļ when you said, ‚ÄúO Moses! We cannot endure the same meal ňĻevery dayňļ. So ňĻjustňļ call upon your Lord on our behalf, He will bring forth for us some of what the earth produces of herbs, cucumbers, garlic, lentils, and onions.‚ÄĚ Moses scolded ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúDo you exchange what is better for what is worse? ňĻYou canňļ go down to any village and you will find what you have asked for.‚ÄĚ They were stricken with disgrace and misery, and they invited the displeasure of Allah for rejecting Allah‚Äôs signs and unjustly killing the prophets. This is ňĻa fair rewardňļ for their disobedience and violations"
  2,62,"Indeed, the believers, Jews, Christians, and Sabians‚ÄĒwhoever ňĻtrulyňļ believes in Allah and the Last Day and does good will have their reward with their Lord. And there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,63,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took a covenant from you and raised the mountain above you ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúHold firmly to that ňĻScriptureňļ which We have given you and observe its teachings so perhaps you will become mindful ňĻof Allahňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  2,64,"Yet you turned away afterwards. Had it not been for Allah‚Äôs grace and mercy upon you, you would have certainly been of the losers"
  2,65,"You are already aware of those of you who broke the Sabbath. We said to them, ‚ÄúBe disgraced apes!‚ÄĚ"
  2,66,"So We made their fate an example to present and future generations, and a lesson to the God-fearing"
  2,67,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Moses said to his people, ‚ÄúAllah commands you to sacrifice a cow.‚ÄĚ¬†They replied, ‚ÄúAre you mocking us?‚ÄĚ Moses responded, ‚ÄúI seek refuge in Allah from acting foolishly!‚ÄĚ"
  2,68,"They said, ‚ÄúCall upon your Lord to clarify for us what type ňĻof cowňļ it should be!‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúAllah says, ‚ÄėThe cow should neither be old nor young but in between. So do as you are commanded!‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  2,69,"They said, ‚ÄúCall upon your Lord to specify for us its colour.‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúAllah says, ‚ÄėIt should be a bright yellow cow‚ÄĒpleasant to see.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  2,70,"Again they said, ‚ÄúCall upon your Lord so that He may make clear to us which cow, for all cows look the same to us. Then, Allah willing, we will be guided ňĻto the right oneňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  2,71,"He replied, ‚ÄúAllah says, ‚ÄėIt should have been used neither to till the soil nor water the fields; wholesome and without blemish.‚Äô‚ÄĚ They said, ‚ÄúNow you have come with the truth.‚ÄĚ Yet they still slaughtered it hesitantly"
  2,72,"ňĻThis isňļ when a man was killed and you disputed who the killer was, but Allah revealed what you concealed"
  2,73,"So We instructed, ‚ÄúStrike the dead body with a piece of the cow.‚ÄĚ This is how ňĻeasilyňļ Allah brings the dead to life, showing you His signs so that you may understand"
  2,74,"Even then your hearts became hardened like a rock or even harder, for some rocks gush rivers; others split, spilling water; while others are humbled in awe of Allah. And Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,75,"Do you ňĻbelievers stillňļ expect them to be true to you, though a group of them would hear the word of Allah then knowingly corrupt it after understanding it"
  2,76,"When they meet the believers they say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ But in private they say ňĻto each otherňļ, ‚ÄúWill you disclose to the believers the knowledge Allah has revealed to you,¬†so that they may use it against you before your Lord? Do you not understand?‚ÄĚ"
  2,77,Do they not know that Allah is aware of what they conceal and what they reveal
  2,78,"And among them are the illiterate who know nothing about the Scripture except lies, and ňĻsoňļ they ňĻwishfullyňļ speculate"
  2,79,"So woe¬†to those who distort the Scripture with their own hands then say, ‚ÄúThis is from Allah‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒseeking a fleeting gain! So woe to them for what their hands have written, and woe to them for what they have earned"
  2,80,"ňĻSome ofňļ the Jews claim, ‚ÄúThe Fire will not touch us except for a number of days.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúHave you taken a pledge from Allah‚ÄĒfor Allah never breaks His word‚ÄĒor are you ňĻjustňļ saying about Allah what you do not know?‚ÄĚ"
  2,81,But no! Those who commit evil and are engrossed in sin will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever
  2,82,And those who believe and do good will be the residents of Paradise. They will be there forever
  2,83,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took a covenant from the children of Israel ňĻstatingňļ, ‚ÄúWorship none but Allah; be kind to parents, relatives, orphans and the needy; speak kindly to people; establish prayer; and pay alms-tax.‚ÄĚ But you ňĻIsraelitesňļ turned away‚ÄĒexcept for a few of you‚ÄĒand were indifferent"
  2,84,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took your covenant that you would neither shed each other‚Äôs blood nor expel each other from their homes, you gave your pledge and bore witness"
  2,85,"But here you are, killing each other and expelling some of your people from their homes, aiding one another in sin and aggression; and when those ňĻexpelledňļ come to you as captives, you still ransom them‚ÄĒthough expelling them was unlawful for you.¬†Do you believe in some of the Scripture and reject the rest? Is there any reward for those who do so among you other than disgrace in this worldly life and being subjected to the harshest punishment on the Day of Judgment? For Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,86,"These are the ones who trade the Hereafter for the life of this world. So their punishment will not be reduced, nor will they be helped"
  2,87,"Indeed, We gave Moses the Book and sent after him successive messengers. And We gave Jesus, son of Mary, clear proofs and supported him with the holy spirit.¬†Why is it that every time a messenger comes to you ňĻIsraelitesňļ with something you do not like, you become arrogant, rejecting some and killing others"
  2,88,"They say, ‚ÄúOur hearts are unreceptive!‚ÄĚ¬†In fact, Allah has condemned them for their disbelief. They have but little faith"
  2,89,"Although they used to pray for victory ňĻby means of the Prophetňļ over the polytheists,¬†when there came to them a Book from Allah which they recognized,¬†confirming the Scripture they had ňĻin their handsňļ, they rejected it. So may Allah‚Äôs condemnation be upon the disbelievers"
  2,90,Miserable is the price they have sold their souls for‚ÄĒdenying Allah‚Äôs revelation and resenting Allah for granting His grace to whoever He wills of His servants! They have earned wrath upon wrath. And such disbelievers will suffer a humiliating punishment
  2,91,"When it is said to them: ‚ÄúBelieve in what Allah has revealed,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúWe only believe in what was sent down to us,‚ÄĚ and they deny what came afterwards, though it is the truth confirming their own Scriptures! Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWhy then did you kill Allah‚Äôs prophets before, if you are ňĻtrulyňļ believers?‚ÄĚ"
  2,92,"Indeed, Moses came to you with clear proofs, then you worshipped the calf in his absence, acting wrongfully"
  2,93,"And when We took your covenant and raised the mountain above you ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúHold firmly to that ňĻScriptureňļ which We have given you and obey,‚ÄĚ they answered, ‚ÄúWe hear and disobey.‚ÄĚ The love of the calf was rooted in their hearts because of their disbelief. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúHow evil is what your ňĻso-calledňļ belief prompts you to do, if you ňĻactuallyňļ believe ňĻin the Torahňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  2,94,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf the ňĻeternalňļ Home of the Hereafter with Allah is exclusively for you ňĻIsraelitesňļ out of all humanity, then wish for death if what you say is true!‚ÄĚ"
  2,95,But they will never wish for that because of what their hands have done.¬†And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of the wrongdoers
  2,96,"You will surely find them clinging to life more eagerly than any other people, even more than polytheists. Each one of them wishes to live a thousand years. But even if they were to live that long, it would not save them from the punishment. And Allah is All-Seeing of what they do"
  2,97,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWhoever is an enemy of Gabriel should know that he revealed this ňĻQuranňļ to your heart by Allah‚Äôs Will, confirming what came before it‚ÄĒa guide and good news for the believers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,98,"Whoever is an enemy of Allah, His angels, His messengers, Gabriel, and Michael, then ňĻlet them know thatňļ Allah is certainly the enemy of the disbelievers"
  2,99,"Indeed, We have sent down to you ňĻO Prophetňļ clear revelations. ňĻButňļ none will deny them except the rebellious"
  2,100,"Why is it that every time they make a covenant, a group of them casts it aside? In fact, most of them do not believe"
  2,101,"Now, when a messenger from Allah has come to them‚ÄĒconfirming their own Scriptures‚ÄĒsome of the People of the Book cast the Book of Allah behind their backs as if they did not know"
  2,102,"They ňĻinsteadňļ followed the magic promoted by the devils during the reign of Solomon. Never did Solomon disbelieve, rather the devils disbelieved. They taught magic to the people, along with what had been revealed to the two angels, H√Ęr√Ľt and M√Ęr√Ľt, in Babylon.¬†The two angels never taught anyone without saying, ‚ÄúWe are only a test ňĻfor youňļ, so do not abandon ňĻyourňļ faith.‚ÄĚ Yet people learned ňĻmagicňļ that caused a rift ňĻevenňļ between husband and wife; although their magic could not harm anyone except by Allah‚Äôs Will. They learned what harmed them and did not benefit them‚ÄĒalthough they already knew that whoever buys into magic would have no share in the Hereafter. Miserable indeed was the price for which they sold their souls, if only they knew"
  2,103,"If only they were faithful and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, there would have been a better reward from Allah, if only they knew"
  2,104,"O believers! Do not say, ‚ÄúR√Ę‚Äôina.‚ÄĚ [Herd us!] But say, ‚ÄúUnŠļďurna,‚ÄĚ [Tend to us!] and listen ňĻattentivelyňļ.¬†And the disbelievers will suffer a painful punishment"
  2,105,"The disbelievers from the People of the Book and the polytheists would not want you to receive any blessing from your Lord, but Allah selects whoever He wills for His mercy. And Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty"
  2,106,"If We ever abrogate¬†a verse or cause it to be forgotten, We replace it with a better or similar one. Do you not know that Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,107,"Do you not know that the kingdom of the heavens and the earth belongs ňĻonlyňļ to Allah, and you have no guardian or helper besides Allah"
  2,108,Or do you ňĻbelieversňļ intend to ask of your Messenger as Moses was asked before?¬†But whoever trades belief for disbelief has truly strayed from the Right Way
  2,109,"Many among the People of the Book wish they could turn you ňĻbelieversňļ back to disbelief because of their envy, after the truth has been made clear to them. Pardon and bear with them until Allah delivers His decision. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,110,"Establish prayer, and pay alms-tax. Whatever good you send forth for yourselves, you will ňĻcertainlyňļ find ňĻits rewardňļ with Allah. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,111,"The Jews and Christians each claim that none will enter Paradise except those of their own faith. These are their desires. Reply, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúShow ňĻmeňļ your proof if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  2,112,"But no! Whoever submits themselves to Allah and does good will have their reward with their Lord. And there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,113,"The Jews say, ‚ÄúThe Christians have nothing to stand on‚ÄĚ and the Christians say, ‚ÄúThe Jews have nothing to stand on,‚ÄĚ although both recite the Scriptures. And those ňĻpagansňļ who have no knowledge say the same ňĻabout people of faithňļ. Surely Allah will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their dispute"
  2,114,"Who does more wrong than those who prevent Allah‚Äôs Name from being mentioned in His places of worship and strive to destroy them? Such people have no right to enter these places except with fear.¬†For them is disgrace in this world, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment in the Hereafter"
  2,115,"To Allah belong the east and the west, so wherever you turn you are facing ňĻtowardsňļ Allah.¬†Surely Allah is All-Encompassing,¬†All-Knowing"
  2,116,"They¬†say, ‚ÄúAllah has offspring.‚ÄĚ¬†Glory be to Him! In fact, to Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒall are subject to His Will"
  2,117,"ňĻHe isňļ the Originator of the heavens and the earth! When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And it is"
  2,118,"Those who have no knowledge say, ‚ÄúIf only Allah would speak to us or a sign would come to us!‚ÄĚ The same was said by those who came before. Their hearts are all alike. Indeed, We have made the signs clear for people of sure faith"
  2,119,We have surely sent you with the truth ňĻO Prophetňļ as a deliverer of good news and a warner. And you will not be accountable for the residents of the Hellfire
  2,120,"Never will the Jews or Christians be pleased with you, until you follow their faith. Say, ‚ÄúAllah‚Äôs guidance is the only ňĻtrueňļ guidance.‚ÄĚ And if you were to follow their desires after ňĻallňļ the knowledge that has come to you, there would be none to protect or help you against Allah"
  2,121,"Those We have given the Book follow it as it should be followed. It is they who ňĻtrulyňļ believe in it. As for those who reject it, it is they who are the losers"
  2,122,O Children of Israel! Remember My favours upon you and how I honoured you above the others
  2,123,"And guard yourselves against the Day when no soul will be of any help to another. No ransom will be taken, no intercession accepted, and no help will be given"
  2,124,"ňĻRememberňļ when Abraham was tested by his Lord with ňĻcertainňļ commandments, which he fulfilled. Allah said, ‚ÄúI will certainly make you into a role model for the people.‚ÄĚ Abraham asked, ‚ÄúWhat about my offspring?‚ÄĚ Allah replied, ‚ÄúMy covenant is not extended to the wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,125,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We made the Sacred House¬†a centre and a sanctuary for the people ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúňĻYou mayňļ take the standing-place of Abraham¬†as a site of prayer.‚ÄĚ And We entrusted Abraham and Ishmael to purify My House for those who circle it, who meditate in it, and who bow and prostrate themselves ňĻin prayerňļ"
  2,126,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham said, ‚ÄúMy Lord, make this city ňĻof Meccaňļ secure and provide fruits to its people‚ÄĒthose among them who believe in Allah and the Last Day.‚ÄĚ He answered, ‚ÄúAs for those who disbelieve, I will let them enjoy themselves for a little while, then I will condemn them to the torment of the Fire. What an evil destination!‚ÄĚ"
  2,127,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham raised the foundation of the House with Ishmael, ňĻboth praying,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! Accept ňĻthisňļ from us. You are indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,128,"Our Lord! Make us both ňĻfullyňļ submit to You¬†and from our descendants a nation that will submit to you. Show us our rituals, and turn to us in grace. You are truly the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,129,"Our Lord! Raise from among them a messenger who will recite to them Your revelations, teach them the Book and wisdom, and purify them. Indeed, You ňĻaloneňļ are the Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  2,130,"And who would reject the faith of Abraham except a fool! We certainly chose him in this life, and in the Hereafter he will surely be among the righteous"
  2,131,"When his Lord ordered him, ‚ÄúSubmit ňĻto My Willňļ,‚ÄĚ he responded, ‚ÄúI submit to the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  2,132,"This was the advice of Abraham‚ÄĒas well as Jacob‚ÄĒto his children, ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúIndeed, Allah has chosen for you this faith; so do not die except in ňĻa state of fullňļ submission.‚ÄĚ"
  2,133,"Or did you witness when death came to Jacob? He asked his children, ‚ÄúWho will you worship after my passing?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúWe will ňĻcontinue toňļ worship your God, the God of your forefathers‚ÄĒAbraham, Ishmael, and Isaac‚ÄĒthe One God. And to Him we ňĻallňļ submit.‚ÄĚ"
  2,134,That was a community that had already gone before. For them is what they earned and for you is what you have earned. And you will not be accountable for what they have done
  2,135,"The Jews and Christians each say, ‚ÄúFollow our faith to be ňĻrightlyňļ guided.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúNo! We follow the faith of Abraham, the upright‚ÄĒwho was not a polytheist.‚ÄĚ"
  2,136,"Say, ňĻO believers,ňļ ‚ÄúWe believe in Allah and what has been revealed to us; and what was revealed to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants; and what was given to Moses, Jesus, and other prophets from their Lord. We make no distinction between any of them. And to Allah we all submit.‚ÄĚ"
  2,137,"So if they believe in what you believe, then they will indeed be ňĻrightlyňļ guided. But if they turn away, they are simply opposed ňĻto the truthňļ. But Allah will spare you their evil. For He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,138,This is the ňĻnaturalňļ Way of Allah. And who is better than Allah in ordaining a way? And we worship ňĻnone butňļ Him
  2,139,"Say, ‚ÄúWould you dispute with us about Allah, while He is our Lord and your Lord? We are accountable for our deeds and you for yours. And we are devoted to Him ňĻaloneňļ"
  2,140,"Do you claim that Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants were all Jews or Christians?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúWho is more knowledgeable: you or Allah?‚ÄĚ Who does more wrong than those who hide the testimony they received from Allah? And Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,141,That was a community that had already gone before. For them is what they earned and for you is what you have earned. And you will not be accountable for what they have done
  2,142,"The foolish among the people will ask, ‚ÄúWhy did they turn away from the direction of prayer they used to face?‚ÄĚ¬†Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúThe east and west belong ňĻonlyňļ to Allah. He guides whoever He wills to the Straight Path.‚ÄĚ"
  2,143,And so We have made you ňĻbelieversňļ an upright¬†community so that you may be witnesses over humanity and that the Messenger may be a witness over you. We assigned your former direction of prayer only to distinguish those who would remain faithful to the Messenger from those who would lose faith. It was certainly a difficult test except for those ňĻrightlyňļ guided by Allah. And Allah would never discount your ňĻprevious acts ofňļ faith. Surely Allah is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to humanity
  2,144,"Indeed, We see you ňĻO Prophetňļ turning your face towards heaven. Now We will make you turn towards a direction ňĻof prayerňļ that will please you. So turn your face towards the Sacred Mosque ňĻin Meccaňļ‚ÄĒwherever you are, turn your faces towards it. Those who were given the Scripture certainly know this to be the truth from their Lord. And Allah is never unaware of what they do"
  2,145,"Even if you were to bring every proof to the People of the Book, they would not accept your direction ňĻof prayerňļ, nor would you accept theirs; nor would any of them accept the direction ňĻof prayerňļ of another. And if you were to follow their desires after ňĻallňļ the knowledge that has come to you, then you would certainly be one of the wrongdoers"
  2,146,Those We have given the Scripture recognize this ňĻProphetňļ as they recognize their own children. Yet a group of them hides the truth knowingly
  2,147,"ňĻThis isňļ the truth from your Lord, so do not ever be one of those who doubt"
  2,148,"Everyone turns to their own direction ňĻof prayerňļ. So compete with one another in doing good. Wherever you are, Allah will bring you all together ňĻfor judgmentňļ. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,149,"Wherever you are ňĻO Prophetňļ, turn your face towards the Sacred Mosque. This is certainly the truth from your Lord. And Allah is never unaware of what you ňĻallňļ do"
  2,150,"Wherever you are ňĻO Prophetňļ, turn your face towards the Sacred Mosque. And wherever you ňĻbelieversňļ are, face towards it, so that people will have no argument against you, except the wrongdoers among them. Do not fear them; fear Me, so that I may ňĻcontinue toňļ perfect My favour upon you and so you may be ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  2,151,"Since We have sent you a messenger from among yourselves‚ÄĒreciting to you Our revelations, purifying you, teaching you the Book and wisdom, and teaching you what you never knew‚ÄĒ"
  2,152,"remember Me; I will remember you. And thank Me, and never be ungrateful"
  2,153,O believers! Seek comfort in patience and prayer. Allah is truly with those who are patient
  2,154,"Never say that those martyred in the cause of Allah are dead‚ÄĒin fact, they are alive! But you do not perceive it"
  2,155,"We will certainly test you with a touch of fear and famine and loss of property, life, and crops. Give good news to those who patiently endure‚ÄĒ"
  2,156,"who, when faced with a disaster, say, ‚ÄúSurely to Allah we belong and to Him we will ňĻallňļ return.‚ÄĚ"
  2,157,They are the ones who will receive Allah‚Äôs blessings and mercy. And it is they who are ňĻrightlyňļ guided
  2,158,"Indeed, ňĻthe hills ofňļ ŠĻĘafa¬†and Marwah¬†are among the symbols of Allah. So whoever performs the pilgrimage or minor pilgrimage,¬†let them walk between ňĻthe two hillsňļ. And whoever does good willingly, Allah is truly Appreciative, All-Knowing"
  2,159,Those who hide the clear proofs and guidance that We have revealed‚ÄĒafter We made it clear for humanity in the Book‚ÄĒwill be condemned by Allah and ňĻallňļ those who condemn
  2,160,"As for those who repent, mend their ways, and let the truth be known, they are the ones to whom I will turn ňĻin forgivenessňļ, for I am the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,161,"Surely those who disbelieve and die as disbelievers are condemned by Allah, the angels, and all of humanity"
  2,162,"They will be in Hell forever. Their punishment will not be lightened, nor will they be delayed ňĻfrom itňļ"
  2,163,"Your God is ňĻonlyňļ One God. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒthe Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  2,164,"Indeed, in the creation of the heavens and the earth; the alternation of the day and the night; the ships that sail the sea for the benefit of humanity; the rain sent down by Allah from the skies, reviving the earth after its death; the scattering of all kinds of creatures throughout; the shifting of the winds; and the clouds drifting between the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒňĻin all of thisňļ are surely signs for people of understanding"
  2,165,"Still there are some who take others as Allah‚Äôs equal‚ÄĒthey love them as they should love Allah‚ÄĒbut the ňĻtrueňļ believers love Allah even more. If only the wrongdoers could see the ňĻhorribleňļ punishment ňĻawaiting themňļ, they would certainly realize that all power belongs to Allah and that Allah is indeed severe in punishment"
  2,166,ňĻConsider the Dayňļ when those who misled others will disown their followers‚ÄĒwhen they face the torment‚ÄĒand the bonds that united them will be cut off
  2,167,"The ňĻmisledňļ followers will cry, ‚ÄúIf only we could have a second chance, we would disown them as they disowned us.‚ÄĚ And so Allah will make them remorseful of their misdeeds. And they will never ňĻbe able toňļ leave the Fire"
  2,168,O humanity! Eat from what is lawful and good on the earth and do not follow Satan‚Äôs footsteps. He is truly your sworn enemy
  2,169,"He only incites you to commit evil and indecency, and to claim against Allah what you do not know"
  2,170,"When it is said to them, ‚ÄúFollow what Allah has revealed,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúNo! We ňĻonlyňļ follow what we found our forefathers practicing.‚ÄĚ ňĻWould they still do so,ňļ even if their forefathers had ňĻabsolutelyňļ no understanding or guidance"
  2,171,"The example of the disbelievers ňĻnot responding to the Messenger‚Äôs warningňļ is like a flock not comprehending the calls and cries of the shepherd. ňĻThey are wilfullyňļ deaf, dumb and blind so they have no understanding"
  2,172,O believers! Eat from the good things We have provided for you. And give thanks to Allah if you ňĻtrulyňļ worship Him ňĻaloneňļ
  2,173,"He has only forbidden you ňĻto eatňļ carrion, blood, swine,¬†and what is slaughtered in the name of any other than Allah. But if someone is compelled by necessity‚ÄĒneither driven by desire nor exceeding immediate need‚ÄĒthey will not be sinful. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,174,"Indeed, those who hide Allah‚Äôs revelations, trading them for a fleeting gain consume nothing but fire into their bellies. Allah will neither speak to them on the Day of Judgment, nor will He purify them. And they will suffer a painful punishment"
  2,175,They are the ones who trade guidance for misguidance and forgiveness for punishment. How persistent are they in pursuit of the Fire
  2,176,That is because Allah has revealed the Book in truth. And surely those who differ regarding it are totally engrossed in opposition
  2,177,"Righteousness is not in turning your faces towards the east or the west. Rather, the righteous are those who believe in Allah, the Last Day, the angels, the Books, and the prophets; who give charity out of their cherished wealth to relatives, orphans, the poor, ňĻneedyňļ travellers, beggars, and for freeing captives; who establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and keep the pledges they make; and who are patient in times of suffering, adversity, and in ňĻthe heat ofňļ battle. It is they who are true ňĻin faithňļ, and it is they who are mindful ňĻof Allahňļ"
  2,178,"O believers! ňĻThe law ofňļ retaliation is set for you in cases of murder‚ÄĒa free man for a free man, a slave for a slave, and a female for a female.¬†But if the offender is pardoned by the victim‚Äôs guardian,¬†then blood-money should be decided fairly¬†and payment should be made courteously. This is a concession and a mercy from your Lord. But whoever transgresses after that will suffer a painful punishment"
  2,179,"There is ňĻsecurity ofňļ life for you in ňĻthe law ofňļ retaliation, O people of reason, so that you may become mindful ňĻof Allahňļ"
  2,180,It is prescribed that when death approaches any of you‚ÄĒif they leave something of value‚ÄĒa will should be made in favour of parents and immediate family with fairness.¬†ňĻThis isňļ an obligation on those who are mindful ňĻof Allahňļ
  2,181,"But whoever changes the will after hearing it,¬†the blame will only be on those who made the change. Indeed, Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,182,"Whoever suspects an error or an injustice in the will and brings about a ňĻfairňļ settlement among the parties will not be sinful. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,183,O believers! Fasting is prescribed for you‚ÄĒas it was for those before you‚ÄĒso perhaps you will become mindful ňĻof Allahňļ
  2,184,"ňĻFast aňļ prescribed number of days.¬†But whoever of you is ill or on a journey, then ňĻlet them fastňļ an equal number of days ňĻafter RamaŠłć√Ęnňļ. For those who can only fast with extreme difficulty,¬†compensation can be made by feeding a needy person ňĻfor every day not fastedňļ. But whoever volunteers to give more, it is better for them. And to fast is better for you, if only you knew"
  2,185,"RamaŠłć√Ęn is the month in which the Quran was revealed as a guide for humanity with clear proofs of guidance and the standard ňĻto distinguish between right and wrongňļ. So whoever is present this month, let them fast. But whoever is ill or on a journey, then ňĻlet them fastňļ an equal number of days ňĻafter RamaŠłć√Ęnňļ. Allah intends ease for you, not hardship, so that you may complete the prescribed period and proclaim the greatness of Allah for guiding you, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  2,186,"When My servants ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about Me: I am truly near. I respond to one‚Äôs prayer when they call upon Me. So let them respond ňĻwith obedienceňļ to Me and believe in Me, perhaps they will be guided ňĻto the Right Wayňļ"
  2,187,"It has been made permissible for you to be intimate with your wives during the nights preceding the fast. Your spouses are a garment¬†for you as you are for them. Allah knows that you were deceiving yourselves.¬†So He has accepted your repentance and pardoned you. So now you may be intimate with them and seek what Allah has prescribed for you.¬†ňĻYou mayňļ eat and drink until you see the light of dawn breaking the darkness of night, then complete the fast until nightfall. Do not be intimate with your spouses while you are meditating in the mosques. These are the limits set by Allah, so do not exceed them. This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to people, so they may become mindful ňĻof Himňļ"
  2,188,"Do not consume one another‚Äôs wealth unjustly, nor deliberately bribe authorities in order to devour a portion of others‚Äô property, knowing that it is a sin"
  2,189,"They ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about the phases of the moon. Say, ‚ÄúThey are a means for people to determine time and pilgrimage.‚ÄĚ Righteousness is not in entering your houses from the back doors.¬†Rather, righteousness is to be mindful ňĻof Allahňļ. So enter your homes through their ňĻproperňļ doors, and be mindful of Allah so you may be successful"
  2,190,"Fight in the cause of Allah ňĻonlyňļ against those who wage war against you, but do not exceed the limits.¬†Allah does not like transgressors"
  2,191,"Kill them wherever you come upon them¬†and drive them out of the places from which they have driven you out. For persecution¬†is far worse than killing. And do not fight them at the Sacred Mosque unless they attack you there. If they do so, then fight them‚ÄĒthat is the reward of the disbelievers"
  2,192,"But if they cease, then surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,193,"Fight against them ňĻif they persecute youňļ until there is no more persecution, and ňĻyourňļ devotion will be to Allah ňĻaloneňļ. If they stop ňĻpersecuting youňļ, let there be no hostility except against the aggressors"
  2,194,"ňĻThere will be retaliation inňļ a sacred month for ňĻan offence inňļ a sacred month,¬†and all violations will bring about retaliation. So, if anyone attacks you, retaliate in the same manner. ňĻButňļ be mindful of Allah, and know that Allah is with those mindful ňĻof Himňļ"
  2,195,"Spend in the cause of Allah and do not let your own hands throw you into destruction ňĻby withholdingňļ. And do good, for Allah certainly loves the good-doers"
  2,196,"Complete the pilgrimage and minor pilgrimage for Allah.¬†But if prevented ňĻfrom proceedingňļ, then ňĻofferňļ whatever sacrificial animals you can afford. And do not shave your heads until the sacrificial animal reaches its destination. But if any of you is ill or has a scalp ailment ňĻrequiring shavingňļ, then compensate either by fasting, charity, or a sacrificial offering. In times of peace, you may combine the pilgrimage and minor pilgrimage then make the sacrificial offering you can afford. Whoever cannot afford that ňĻofferingňļ, let them fast three days during pilgrimage and seven after returning ňĻhomeňļ‚ÄĒcompleting ten. These offerings are for those who do not live near the Sacred House. And be mindful of Allah, and know that Allah is severe in punishment"
  2,197,"ňĻCommitment toňļ pilgrimage is made in appointed months.¬†Whoever commits to ňĻperformingňļ pilgrimage, let them stay away from intimate relations, foul language, and arguments during pilgrimage. Whatever good you do, Allah ňĻfullyňļ knows of it. Take ňĻnecessaryňļ provisions ňĻfor the journeyňļ‚ÄĒsurely the best provision is righteousness. And be mindful of Me, O people of reason"
  2,198,"There is no blame on you for seeking the bounty of your Lord ňĻduring this journeyňļ.¬†When you return from ‚ÄôAraf√Ęt,¬†praise Allah near the sacred place¬†and praise Him for having guided you, for surely before this ňĻguidanceňļ you were astray"
  2,199,"Then go forth with the rest of the pilgrims. And seek Allah‚Äôs forgiveness. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,200,"When you have fulfilled your sacred rites, praise Allah as you used to praise your forefathers ňĻbefore Islamňļ, or even more passionately. There are some who say, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Grant us ňĻYour bountiesňļ in this world,‚ÄĚ but they will have no share in the Hereafter"
  2,201,"Yet there are others who say, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Grant us the good of this world and the Hereafter, and protect us from the torment of the Fire.‚ÄĚ"
  2,202,It is they who will receive a ňĻheavenlyňļ reward for the good they have done. Surely Allah is swift in reckoning
  2,203,"And remember Allah during ňĻtheseňļ appointed days.¬†Whoever departs swiftly on the second day is not sinful, neither are those who stay behind ňĻtill the third‚ÄĒseeking additional rewardňļ, so long as they are mindful ňĻof their Lordňļ. And be mindful of Allah, and know that to Him you will ňĻallňļ be gathered"
  2,204,"There are some ňĻhypocritesňļ who impress you with their views regarding worldly affairs and openly call upon Allah to witness what is in their hearts, yet they are your worst adversaries"
  2,205,"And when they leave ňĻyouňļ,¬†they strive throughout the land to spread mischief in it and destroy crops and cattle. Allah does not like mischief"
  2,206,"When it is said to them, ‚ÄúFear Allah,‚ÄĚ pride carries them off to sin. Hell will be their proper place. What an evil place to rest"
  2,207,And there are those who would dedicate their lives to Allah‚Äôs pleasure. And Allah is Ever Gracious to ňĻHisňļ servants
  2,208,O believers! Enter into Islam wholeheartedly and do not follow Satan‚Äôs footsteps. Surely he is your sworn enemy
  2,209,"If you falter after receiving the clear proofs, then know that Allah is indeed Almighty, All-Wise"
  2,210,"Are they waiting for Allah ňĻHimselfňļ to come to them in the shade of clouds, along with the angels? ňĻIf He didňļ, then the matter would be settled ňĻat onceňļ. And to Allah ňĻallňļ matters will be returned ňĻfor judgmentňļ"
  2,211,Ask the Children of Israel how many clear signs We have given them. And whoever trades Allah‚Äôs favour‚ÄĒafter receiving it‚ÄĒňĻfor disbeliefňļ should know that Allah is indeed severe in punishment
  2,212,"The life of this world has been made appealing to the disbelievers, and they mock the believers. Those who are mindful ňĻof Allahňļ will rank above them on the Day of Judgment. And Allah provides for whoever He wills without limit"
  2,213,"Humanity had once been one community ňĻof believers before they lost faithňļ. Then Allah raised prophets as deliverers of good news and as warners, and revealed to them the Scriptures in truth to judge among people regarding their disputes. And no one disputed the Scriptures except the very people who received them after clear proofs had come to them‚ÄĒout of jealousy. Then Allah, by His grace, has guided the believers to the truth regarding those disputes. And Allah guides whoever He wills to the Straight Path"
  2,214,"Do you think you will be admitted into Paradise without being tested like those before you? They were afflicted with suffering and adversity and were so ňĻviolentlyňļ shaken that ňĻevenňļ the Messenger and the believers with him cried out, ‚ÄúWhen will Allah‚Äôs help come?‚ÄĚ Indeed, Allah‚Äôs help is ňĻalwaysňļ near"
  2,215,"They ask you ňĻO Prophet inňļ what ňĻwayňļ they should donate. Say, ‚ÄúWhatever donations you give are for parents, relatives, orphans, the poor, and ňĻneedyňļ travellers. Whatever good you do is certainly well known to Allah.‚ÄĚ"
  2,216,"Fighting has been made obligatory upon you ňĻbelieversňļ, though you dislike it. Perhaps you dislike something which is good for you and like something which is bad for you. Allah knows and you do not know"
  2,217,"They¬†ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about fighting in the sacred months.¬†Say, ‚ÄúFighting during these months is a great sin. But hindering ňĻothersňļ from the Path of Allah, rejecting Him, and expelling the worshippers from the Sacred Mosque is ňĻaňļ greater ňĻsinňļ in the sight of Allah. For persecution¬†is far worse than killing. And they will not stop fighting you until they turn you away from your faith‚ÄĒif they can. And whoever among you renounces their own faith and dies a disbeliever, their deeds will become void in this life and in the Hereafter. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever.‚ÄĚ"
  2,218,"Surely those who have believed, emigrated, and struggled in the Way of Allah‚ÄĒthey can hope for Allah‚Äôs mercy. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,219,"They ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about intoxicants and gambling. Say, ‚ÄúThere is great evil in both, as well as some benefit for people‚ÄĒbut the evil outweighs the benefit.‚ÄĚ¬†They ňĻalsoňļ ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ what they should donate. Say, ‚ÄúWhatever you can spare.‚ÄĚ This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you ňĻbelieversňļ, so perhaps you may reflect"
  2,220,"upon this world and the Hereafter. And they ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ concerning orphans. Say, ‚ÄúImproving their condition is best. And if you partner with them, they are bonded with you ňĻin faithňļ.¬†And Allah knows who intends harm and who intends good. Had Allah willed, He could have made it difficult for you.¬†Surely Allah is Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  2,221,"Do not marry polytheistic women until they believe; for a believing slave-woman is better than a free polytheist, even though she may look pleasant to you. And do not marry your women to polytheistic men until they believe, for a believing slave-man is better than a free polytheist, even though he may look pleasant to you. They invite ňĻyouňļ to the Fire while Allah invites ňĻyouňļ to Paradise and forgiveness by His grace.¬†He makes His revelations clear to the people so perhaps they will be mindful"
  2,222,"They ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about menstruation. Say, ‚ÄúBeware of its harm! So keep away, and do not have intercourse with your wives during their monthly cycles until they are purified.¬†When they purify themselves, then you may approach them in the manner specified by Allah. Surely Allah loves those who always turn to Him in repentance and those who purify themselves.‚ÄĚ"
  2,223,"Your wives are like farmland for you,¬†so approach them ňĻconsensuallyňļ as you please.¬†And send forth something good for yourselves.¬†Be mindful of Allah, and know that you will meet Him. And give good news to the believers"
  2,224,"Do not use Allah‚Äôs Name in your oaths as an excuse for not doing good, not guarding against evil, or not making peace between people. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,225,"Allah will not hold you accountable for unintentional oaths, but for what you intended in your hearts. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  2,226,"Those who swear not to have intercourse with their wives must wait for four months.¬†If they change their mind, then Allah is certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,227,"But if they settle on divorce, then Allah is indeed All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,228,"Divorced women must wait three monthly cycles ňĻbefore they can re-marryňļ. It is not lawful for them to conceal what Allah has created in their wombs,¬†if they ňĻtrulyňļ believe in Allah and the Last Day. And their husbands reserve the right to take them back within that period if they desire reconciliation. Women have rights similar to those of men equitably, although men have a degree ňĻof responsibilityňļ above them. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  2,229,"Divorce may be retracted twice, then the husband must retain ňĻhis wifeňļ with honour or separate ňĻfrom herňļ with grace.¬†It is not lawful for husbands to take back anything of the dowry given to their wives, unless the couple fears not being able to keep within the limits of Allah.¬†So if you fear they will not be able to keep within the limits of Allah, there is no blame if the wife compensates the husband to obtain divorce.¬†These are the limits set by Allah, so do not transgress them. And whoever transgresses the limits of Allah, they are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  2,230,"So if a husband divorces his wife ňĻthree timesňļ, then it is not lawful for him to remarry her until after she has married another man and then is divorced. Then it is permissible for them to reunite, as long as they feel they are able to maintain the limits of Allah. These are the limits set by Allah, which He makes clear for people of knowledge"
  2,231,"When you divorce women and they have ňĻalmostňļ reached the end of their waiting period, either retain them honourably or let them go honourably. But do not retain them ňĻonlyňļ to harm them ňĻorňļ to take advantage ňĻof themňļ. Whoever does that surely wrongs his own soul. Do not take Allah‚Äôs revelations lightly. Remember Allah‚Äôs favours upon you as well as the Book and wisdom¬†He has sent down for your guidance. Be mindful of Allah, and know that Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  2,232,"When you have divorced women and they have reached the end of their waiting period, do not prevent them from re-marrying their ex-husbands if they come to an honourable agreement. This is enjoined on whoever has faith in Allah and the Last Day. This is purer and more dignifying for you. Allah knows and you do not know"
  2,233,"ňĻDivorcedňļ mothers will breastfeed their offspring for two whole years, for those who wish to complete the nursing ňĻof their childňļ. The child‚Äôs father will provide reasonable maintenance and clothing for the mother ňĻduring that periodňļ. No one will be charged with more than they can bear. No mother or father should be made to suffer for their child. The ňĻfather‚Äôsňļ heirs are under the same obligation. But if both sides decide‚ÄĒafter mutual consultation and consent‚ÄĒto wean a child, then there is no blame on them. If you decide to have your children nursed by a wet-nurse, it is permissible as long as you pay fairly. Be mindful of Allah, and know that Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,234,"As for those of you who die and leave widows behind, let them observe a waiting period of four months and ten days. When they have reached the end of this period, then you¬†are not accountable for what they decide for themselves in a reasonable manner. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  2,235,"There is no blame on you for subtly showing interest in ňĻdivorced or widowedňļ women¬†or for hiding ňĻthe intentionňļ in your hearts. Allah knows that you are considering them ňĻfor marriageňļ. But do not make a secret commitment with them‚ÄĒyou can only show interest in them appropriately. Do not commit to the bond of marriage until the waiting period expires. Know that Allah is aware of what is in your hearts, so beware of Him. And know that Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  2,236,There is no blame if you divorce women before the marriage is consummated or the dowry is settled. But give them a ňĻsuitableňļ compensation‚ÄĒthe rich according to his means and the poor according to his. A reasonable compensation is an obligation on the good-doers
  2,237,"And if you divorce them before consummating the marriage but after deciding on a dowry, pay half of the dowry, unless the wife graciously waives it or the husband graciously pays in full. Graciousness is closer to righteousness. And do not forget kindness among yourselves. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,238,Observe the ňĻfive obligatoryňļ prayers‚ÄĒespecially the middle prayer‚ÄĒand stand in true devotion to Allah
  2,239,"If you are in danger, pray on foot or while riding. But when you are safe, ňĻtake time toňļ remember Allah for teaching you what you did not know"
  2,240,"Those of you who die leaving widows should bequeath for them a year‚Äôs maintenance without forcing them out.¬†But if they choose to leave, you are not accountable for what they reasonably decide for themselves. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  2,241,Reasonable provisions must be made for divorced women‚ÄĒa duty on those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ
  2,242,"This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, so perhaps you will understand"
  2,243,"Have you ňĻO Prophetňļ not seen those who fled their homes in the thousands for fear of death?¬†Allah said to them, ‚ÄúDie!‚ÄĚ then He gave them life. Surely Allah is ever Bountiful to humanity, but most people are ungrateful"
  2,244,"Fight in the cause of Allah, and know that Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,245,Who will lend to Allah a good loan which Allah will multiply many times over? It is Allah ňĻaloneňļ who decreases and increases ňĻwealthňļ. And to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned
  2,246,"Have you not seen those chiefs of the Children of Israel after Moses? They said to one of their prophets, ‚ÄúAppoint for us a king, ňĻandňļ we will fight in the cause of Allah.‚ÄĚ He said, ‚ÄúAre you not going to cower if ordered to fight?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúHow could we refuse to fight in the cause of Allah, while we were driven out of our homes and ňĻseparated fromňļ our children?‚ÄĚ But when they were ordered to fight, they fled, except for a few of them. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of the wrongdoers"
  2,247,"Their prophet told them, ‚ÄúAllah has appointed Saul¬†to be your king.‚ÄĚ They protested, ‚ÄúHow can he be our king when some of us are more deserving of kingship than he, and he has not been blessed with vast riches?‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúAllah has chosen him over you and blessed him with knowledge and stature. Allah grants kingship to whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing.‚ÄĚ"
  2,248,"Their prophet further told them, ‚ÄúThe sign of Saul‚Äôs kingship is that the Ark will come to you‚ÄĒcontaining reassurance¬†from your Lord and relics of the family of Moses and the family of Aaron,¬†which will be carried by the angels. Surely in this is a sign for you, if you ňĻtrulyňļ believe.‚ÄĚ"
  2,249,"When Saul marched forth with his army, he cautioned: ‚ÄúAllah will test you with a river. So whoever drinks ňĻhis fillňļ from it is not with me, and whoever does not taste it‚ÄĒexcept a sip from the hollow of his hands‚ÄĒis definitely with me.‚ÄĚ They all drank ňĻtheir fillňļ except for a few! When he and the ňĻremainingňļ faithful with him crossed the river, they said, ‚ÄúNow we are no match for Goliath and his warriors.‚ÄĚ But those ňĻbelieversňļ who were certain they would meet Allah reasoned, ‚ÄúHow many times has a small force vanquished a mighty army by the Will of Allah! And Allah is ňĻalwaysňļ with the steadfast.‚ÄĚ"
  2,250,"When they advanced to face Goliath and his warriors, they prayed, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Shower us with perseverance, make our steps firm, and give us victory over the disbelieving people.‚ÄĚ"
  2,251,"So they defeated them by Allah‚Äôs Will, and David killed Goliath. And Allah blessed David with kingship and wisdom and taught him what He willed. Had Allah not repelled a group of people by ňĻthe might ofňļ another, corruption would have dominated the earth, but Allah is Gracious to all"
  2,252,These are Allah‚Äôs revelations which We recite to you ňĻO Prophetňļ in truth. And you are truly one of the messengers
  2,253,"We have chosen some of those messengers above others.¬†Allah spoke directly to some, and raised some high in rank. To Jesus, son of Mary, We gave clear proofs and supported him with the holy spirit.¬†If Allah had willed, succeeding generations would not have fought ňĻamong themselvesňļ after receiving the clear proofs. But they differed‚ÄĒsome believed while others disbelieved. Yet if Allah had willed, they would not have fought one another. But Allah does what He wills"
  2,254,"O believers! Donate from what We have provided for you before the arrival of a Day when there will be no bargaining,¬†friendship,¬†or intercession. Those who disbelieve are ňĻtrulyňļ the wrongdoers"
  2,255,"Allah! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him, the Ever-Living, All-Sustaining. Neither drowsiness nor sleep overtakes Him. To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Who could possibly intercede with Him without His permission? He ňĻfullyňļ knows what is ahead of them and what is behind them, but no one can grasp any of His knowledge‚ÄĒexcept what He wills ňĻto revealňļ. His Seat¬†encompasses the heavens and the earth, and the preservation of both does not tire Him. For He is the Most High, the Greatest"
  2,256,"Let there be no compulsion in religion, for the truth stands out clearly from falsehood.¬†So whoever renounces false gods and believes in Allah has certainly grasped the firmest, unfailing hand-hold. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,257,"Allah is the Guardian of the believers‚ÄĒHe brings them out of darkness and into light. As for the disbelievers, their guardians are false gods who lead them out of light and into darkness. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  2,258,"Are you ňĻO Prophetňļ not aware of the one who argued with Abraham about his Lord because Allah had granted him kingship? ňĻRememberňļ when Abraham said, ‚ÄúMy Lord is the One Who has power to give life and cause death.‚ÄĚ He argued, ‚ÄúI too have the power to give life and cause death.‚ÄĚ Abraham challenged ňĻhimňļ, ‚ÄúAllah causes the sun to rise from the east. So make it rise from the west.‚ÄĚ And so the disbeliever was dumbstruck. And Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  2,259,"Or ňĻare you not aware ofňļ the one who passed by a city which was in ruins. He wondered, ‚ÄúHow could Allah bring this back to life after its destruction?‚ÄĚ So Allah caused him to die for a hundred years then brought him back to life. Allah asked, ‚ÄúHow long have you remained ňĻin this stateňļ?‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúPerhaps a day or part of a day.‚ÄĚ Allah said, ‚ÄúNo! You have remained here for a hundred years! Just look at your food and drink‚ÄĒthey have not spoiled. ňĻBut nowňļ look at ňĻthe remains ofňļ your donkey! And ňĻsoňļ We have made you into a sign for humanity. And look at the bones ňĻof the donkeyňļ, how We bring them together then clothe them with flesh!‚ÄĚ¬†When this was made clear to him, he declared, ‚ÄúňĻNowňļ I know that Allah is Most Capable of everything.‚ÄĚ"
  2,260,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Show me how you give life to the dead.‚ÄĚ Allah responded, ‚ÄúDo you not believe?‚ÄĚ Abraham replied, ‚ÄúYes I do, but just so my heart can be reassured.‚ÄĚ Allah said, ‚ÄúThen bring four birds, train them to come to you, ňĻthen cut them into pieces,ňļ and scatter them on different hilltops. Then call them back, they will fly to you in haste. And ňĻso you willňļ know that Allah is Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  2,261,"The example of those who spend their wealth in the cause of Allah is that of a grain that sprouts into seven ears, each bearing one hundred grains. And Allah multiplies ňĻthe reward even moreňļ to whoever He wills. For Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing"
  2,262,"Those who spend their wealth in the cause of Allah and do not follow their charity with reminders of their generosity or hurtful words‚ÄĒthey will get their reward from their Lord, and there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,263,"Kind words and forgiveness are better than charity followed by injury. And Allah is Self-Sufficient, Most Forbearing"
  2,264,"O believers! Do not waste your charity with reminders ňĻof your generosityňļ or hurtful words, like those who donate their wealth just to show off and do not believe in Allah or the Last Day. Their example is that of a hard barren rock covered with a thin layer of soil hit by a strong rain‚ÄĒleaving it just a bare stone. Such people are unable to preserve the reward of their charity. Allah does not guide ňĻsuchňļ disbelieving people"
  2,265,"And the example of those who donate their wealth, seeking Allah‚Äôs pleasure and believing the reward is certain,¬†is that of a garden on a fertile hill: when heavy rain falls, it yields up twice its normal produce. If no heavy rain falls, a drizzle is sufficient. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,266,"Would any of you wish to have a garden with palm trees, grapevines, and all kinds of fruits with rivers flowing underneath and as they grow very old with dependent children, a fiery whirlwind hits the garden, burning it all up? This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, so perhaps you will reflect"
  2,267,"O believers! Donate from the best of what you have earned and of what We have produced for you from the earth. Do not pick out worthless things for donation, which you yourselves would only accept with closed eyes. And know that Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  2,268,"The Devil threatens you with ňĻthe prospect ofňļ poverty and bids you to the shameful deed ňĻof stinginessňļ, while Allah promises you forgiveness and ňĻgreatňļ bounties from Him. And Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing"
  2,269,Allah grants wisdom to whoever He wills. And whoever is granted wisdom is certainly blessed with a great privilege. But none will be mindful ňĻof thisňļ except people of reason
  2,270,Whatever charities you give or vows you make are surely known to Allah. And the wrongdoers will have no helpers
  2,271,"To give charity publicly is good, but to give to the poor privately is better for you, and will absolve you of your sins. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  2,272,"You are not responsible for people‚Äôs guidance ňĻO Prophetňļ‚ÄĒit is Allah Who guides whoever He wills. Whatever you ňĻbelieversňļ spend in charity, it is for your own good‚ÄĒas long as you do so seeking the pleasure of Allah.¬†Whatever you donate will be paid back to you in full, and you will not be wronged"
  2,273,ňĻCharity isňļ for the needy who are too engaged in the cause of Allah to move about in the land ňĻfor workňļ. Those unfamiliar with their situation will think they are not in need ňĻof charityňļ because they do not beg. You can recognize them by their appearance. They do not beg people persistently. Whatever you give in charity is certainly well known to Allah
  2,274,"Those who spend their wealth in charity day and night, secretly and openly‚ÄĒtheir reward is with their Lord, and there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,275,"Those who consume interest will stand ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ like those driven to madness by Satan‚Äôs touch. That is because they say, ‚ÄúTrade is no different than interest.‚ÄĚ But Allah has permitted trading and forbidden interest. Whoever refrains‚ÄĒafter having received warning from their Lord‚ÄĒmay keep their previous gains, and their case is left to Allah. As for those who persist, it is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  2,276,Allah has made interest fruitless and charity fruitful. And Allah does not like any ungrateful evildoer
  2,277,"Indeed, those who believe, do good, establish prayer, and pay alms-tax will receive their reward from their Lord, and there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,278,"O believers! Fear Allah, and give up outstanding interest if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  2,279,"If you do not, then beware of a war with Allah and His Messenger! But if you repent, you may retain your principal‚ÄĒneither inflicting nor suffering harm"
  2,280,"If it is difficult for someone to repay a debt, postpone it until a time of ease. And if you waive it as an act of charity, it will be better for you, if only you knew"
  2,281,"Be mindful of the Day when you will ňĻallňļ be returned to Allah, then every soul will be paid in full for what it has done, and none will be wronged"
  2,282,"O believers! When you contract a loan for a fixed period of time, commit it to writing. Let the scribe maintain justice between the parties. The scribe should not refuse to write as Allah has taught them to write. They will write what the debtor dictates, bearing Allah in mind and not defrauding the debt. If the debtor is incompetent, weak, or unable to dictate, let their guardian dictate for them with justice. Call upon two of your men to witness. If two men cannot be found, then one man and two women of your choice will witness‚ÄĒso if one of the women forgets the other may remind her.¬†The witnesses must not refuse when they are summoned. You must not be against writing ňĻcontractsňļ for a fixed period‚ÄĒwhether the sum is small or great. This is more just ňĻfor youňļ in the sight of Allah, and more convenient to establish evidence and remove doubts. However, if you conduct an immediate transaction among yourselves, then there is no need for you to record it, but call upon witnesses when a deal is finalized. Let no harm come to the scribe or witnesses. If you do, then you have gravely exceeded ňĻyour limitsňļ. Be mindful of Allah, for Allah ňĻis the One Whoňļ teaches you. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  2,283,"If you are on a journey and a scribe cannot be found, then a security can be taken. If you trust one another, then ňĻthere is no need for a security, butňļ the debtor should honour this trust ňĻby repaying the debtňļ‚ÄĒand let them fear Allah, their Lord. And do not conceal the testimony, for whoever conceals it, their hearts are indeed sinful. And Allah ňĻfullyňļ knows what you do"
  2,284,"To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Whether you reveal what is in your hearts or conceal it, Allah will call you to account for it. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,285,"The Messenger ňĻfirmlyňļ believes in what has been revealed to him from his Lord, and so do the believers. They ňĻallňļ believe in Allah, His angels, His Books, and His messengers. ňĻThey proclaim,ňļ ‚ÄúWe make no distinction between any of His messengers.‚ÄĚ And they say, ‚ÄúWe hear and obey. ňĻWe seekňļ Your forgiveness, our Lord! And to You ňĻaloneňļ is the final return.‚ÄĚ"
  2,286,"Allah does not require of any soul more than what it can afford. All good will be for its own benefit, and all evil will be to its own loss. ňĻThe believers pray,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! Do not punish us if we forget or make a mistake. Our Lord! Do not place a burden on us like the one you placed on those before us. Our Lord! Do not burden us with what we cannot bear. Pardon us, forgive us, and have mercy on us. You are our ňĻonlyňļ Guardian. So grant us victory over the disbelieving people.‚ÄĚ"
  3,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m
  3,2,"Allah! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒthe Ever-Living, All-Sustaining"
  3,3,"He has revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ the Book in truth, confirming what came before it, as He revealed the Torah and the Gospel"
  3,4,"previously, as a guide for people, and ňĻalsoňļ revealed the Standard ňĻto distinguish between right and wrongňļ.¬†Surely those who reject Allah‚Äôs revelations will suffer a severe torment. For Allah is Almighty, capable of punishment"
  3,5,Surely nothing on earth or in the heavens is hidden from Allah
  3,6,"He is the One Who shapes you in the wombs of your mothers as He wills. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,7,"He is the One Who has revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ the Book, of which some verses are precise‚ÄĒthey are the foundation of the Book‚ÄĒwhile others are elusive.¬†Those with deviant hearts follow the elusive verses seeking ňĻto spreadňļ doubt through their ňĻfalseňļ interpretations‚ÄĒbut none grasps their ňĻfullňļ meaning except Allah. As for those well-grounded in knowledge, they say, ‚ÄúWe believe in this ňĻQuranňļ‚ÄĒit is all from our Lord.‚ÄĚ But none will be mindful ňĻof thisňļ except people of reason"
  3,8,"ňĻThey say,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! Do not let our hearts deviate after you have guided us. Grant us Your mercy. You are indeed the Giver ňĻof all bountiesňļ"
  3,9,Our Lord! You will certainly gather all humanity for the ňĻpromisedňļ Day‚ÄĒabout which there is no doubt. Surely Allah does not break His promise.‚ÄĚ
  3,10,"Indeed, neither the wealth nor children¬†of the disbelievers will be of any benefit to them against Allah‚ÄĒand they will be the fuel for the Fire"
  3,11,"Their fate will be like that of the people of Pharaoh and those before them‚ÄĒthey all rejected Our signs, so Allah seized them for their sins. And Allah is severe in punishment"
  3,12,"ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Tell the disbelievers, ‚ÄúSoon you will be overpowered and driven to Hell‚ÄĒwhat an evil place to rest!‚ÄĚ"
  3,13,"Indeed, there was a sign for you in the two armies that met in battle‚ÄĒone fighting for the cause of Allah and the other in denial. The believers saw their enemy twice their number.¬†But Allah supports with His victory whoever He wills. Surely in this is a lesson for people of insight"
  3,14,"The enjoyment of ňĻworldlyňļ desires‚ÄĒwomen, children,¬†treasures of gold and silver, fine horses, cattle, and fertile land‚ÄĒhas been made appealing to people. These are the pleasures of this worldly life, but with Allah is the finest destination"
  3,15,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúShall I inform you of what is better than ňĻall ofňļ this? Those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ will have Gardens with their Lord under which rivers flow, to stay there forever, and pure spouses,¬†along with Allah‚Äôs pleasure.‚ÄĚ And Allah is All-Seeing of ňĻHisňļ servants"
  3,16,"who pray, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We have believed, so forgive our sins and protect us from the torment of the Fire.‚ÄĚ"
  3,17,"ňĻIt is theyňļ who are patient, sincere, obedient, and charitable, and who pray for forgiveness before dawn"
  3,18,"Allah ňĻHimselfňļ is a Witness that there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒand so are the angels and people of knowledge. He is the Maintainer of justice. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,19,"Certainly, Allah‚Äôs only Way is Islam.¬†Those who were given the Scripture did not dispute ňĻamong themselvesňļ out of mutual envy until knowledge came to them.¬†Whoever denies Allah‚Äôs signs, then surely Allah is swift in reckoning"
  3,20,"So if they argue with you ňĻO Prophetňļ, say, ‚ÄúI have submitted myself to Allah, and so have my followers.‚ÄĚ And ask those who were given the Scripture and the illiterate ňĻpeopleňļ,¬†‚ÄúHave you submitted yourselves ňĻto Allahňļ?‚ÄĚ If they submit, they will be ňĻrightlyňļ guided. But if they turn away, then your duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ. And Allah is All-Seeing of ňĻHisňļ servants"
  3,21,"Indeed, those who deny Allah‚Äôs signs, kill the prophets unjustly, and kill people who stand up for justice‚ÄĒgive them good news of a painful punishment"
  3,22,They are the ones whose deeds are wasted in this world and the Hereafter. And they will have no helpers
  3,23,"Have you not seen those who were given a portion of the Scriptures?¬†Yet when they are invited to the Book of Allah to settle their disputes, some of them turn away heedlessly"
  3,24,"This is because they say, ‚ÄúThe Fire will not touch us except for a few days.‚ÄĚ They have been deceived in their faith by their wishful lying"
  3,25,"But how ňĻhorribleňļ will it be when We gather them together on the Day about which there is no doubt‚ÄĒwhen every soul will be paid in full for what it has done, and none will be wronged"
  3,26,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO Allah! Lord over all authorities! You give authority to whoever You please and remove it from who You please; You honour whoever You please and disgrace who You please‚ÄĒall good is in Your Hands. Surely You ňĻaloneňļ are Most Capable of everything"
  3,27,You cause the night to pass into the day and the day into the night. You bring forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living. And You provide for whoever You will without limit.‚ÄĚ
  3,28,Believers should not take disbelievers as guardians instead of the believers‚ÄĒand whoever does so will have nothing to hope for from Allah‚ÄĒunless it is a precaution against their tyranny. And Allah warns you about Himself. And to Allah is the final return
  3,29,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWhether you conceal what is in your hearts or reveal it, it is known to Allah. For He knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And Allah is Most Capable of everything.‚ÄĚ"
  3,30,ňĻWatch forňļ the Day when every soul will be presented with whatever good it has done. And it will wish that its misdeeds were far off. And Allah warns you about Himself. And Allah is Ever Gracious to ňĻHisňļ servants
  3,31,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf you ňĻsincerelyňļ love Allah, then follow me; Allah will love you and forgive your sins. For Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  3,32,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúObey Allah and His Messenger.‚ÄĚ If they still turn away, then truly Allah does not like the disbelievers"
  3,33,"Indeed, Allah chose Adam, Noah, the family of Abraham, and the family of ‚ÄôImr√Ęn above all people ňĻof their timeňļ"
  3,34,"They are descendants of one another. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,35,"ňĻRememberňļ when the wife of ‚ÄôImr√Ęn said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I dedicate what is in my womb entirely to Your service,¬†so accept it from me. You ňĻaloneňļ are truly the All-Hearing, All-Knowing.‚ÄĚ"
  3,36,"When she delivered, she said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I have given birth to a girl,‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒand Allah fully knew what she had delivered‚ÄĒ‚Äúand the male is not like the female.¬†I have named her Mary, and I seek Your protection for her and her offspring from Satan, the accursed.‚ÄĚ"
  3,37,"So her Lord accepted her graciously and blessed her with a pleasant upbringing‚ÄĒentrusting her to the care of Zachariah. Whenever Zachariah visited her in the sanctuary, he found her supplied with provisions. He exclaimed, ‚ÄúO Mary! Where did this come from?‚ÄĚ She replied, ‚ÄúIt is from Allah. Surely Allah provides for whoever He wills without limit.‚ÄĚ"
  3,38,"Then and there Zachariah prayed to his Lord, saying, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Grant me‚ÄĒby your grace‚ÄĒrighteous offspring. You are certainly the Hearer of ňĻallňļ prayers.‚ÄĚ"
  3,39,"So the angels called out to him while he stood praying in the sanctuary, ‚ÄúAllah gives you good news of ňĻthe birth ofňļ John who will confirm the Word of Allah and will be a great leader, chaste, and a prophet among the righteous.‚ÄĚ"
  3,40,"Zachariah exclaimed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! How can I have a son when I am very old and my wife is barren?‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúSo will it be. Allah does what He wills.‚ÄĚ"
  3,41,"Zachariah said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Grant me a sign.‚ÄĚ He said, ‚ÄúYour sign is that you will not ňĻbe able toňļ speak to people for three days except through gestures. Remember your Lord often and glorify ňĻHimňļ morning and evening.‚ÄĚ"
  3,42,"And ňĻrememberňļ when the angels said, ‚ÄúO Mary! Surely Allah has selected you, purified you, and chosen you over all women of the world"
  3,43,"O Mary! Be devout to your Lord, prostrate yourself ňĻin prayerňļ and bow along with those who bow down.‚ÄĚ"
  3,44,"This is news of the unseen that We reveal to you ňĻO Prophetňļ. You were not with them when they cast lots to decide who would be Mary‚Äôs guardian, nor were you there when they argued ňĻabout itňļ"
  3,45,"ňĻRememberňļ when the angels proclaimed, ‚ÄúO Mary! Allah gives you good news of a Word¬†from Him, his name will be the Messiah,¬†Jesus, son of Mary; honoured in this world and the Hereafter, and he will be one of those nearest ňĻto Allahňļ"
  3,46,And he will speak to people in ňĻhisňļ infancy and adulthood and will be one of the righteous.‚ÄĚ
  3,47,"Mary wondered, ‚ÄúMy Lord! How can I have a child when no man has ever touched me?‚ÄĚ An angel replied, ‚ÄúSo will it be. Allah creates what He wills. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, ‚ÄėBe!‚Äô And it is"
  3,48,"And Allah will teach him writing and wisdom, the Torah and the Gospel"
  3,49,"and ňĻmake himňļ a messenger to the Children of Israel ňĻto proclaim,ňļ ‚ÄėI have come to you with a sign from your Lord: I will make for you a bird from clay, breathe into it, and it will become a ňĻrealňļ bird‚ÄĒby Allah‚Äôs Will. I will heal the blind and the leper and raise the dead to life‚ÄĒby Allah‚Äôs Will. And I will prophesize what you eat and store in your houses. Surely in this is a sign for you if you ňĻtrulyňļ believe"
  3,50,"And I will confirm the Torah revealed before me and legalize some of what had been forbidden to you. I have come to you with a sign from your Lord, so be mindful of Allah and obey me"
  3,51,Surely Allah is my Lord and your Lord. So worship Him ňĻaloneňļ. This is the Straight Path.‚Äô‚ÄĚ
  3,52,"When Jesus sensed disbelief from his people, he asked, ‚ÄúWho will stand up with me for Allah?‚ÄĚ The disciples replied, ‚ÄúWe will stand up for Allah. We believe in Allah, so bear witness that we have submitted.‚ÄĚ"
  3,53,"ňĻThey prayed to Allah,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! We believe in Your revelations and follow the messenger, so count us among those who bear witness.‚ÄĚ"
  3,54,"And the disbelievers made a plan ňĻagainst Jesusňļ, but Allah also planned‚ÄĒand Allah is the best of planners"
  3,55,"ňĻRememberňļ when Allah said, ‚ÄúO Jesus! I will take you¬†and raise you up to Myself. I will deliver you from those who disbelieve, and elevate your followers above the disbelievers until the Day of Judgment. Then to Me you will ňĻallňļ return, and I will settle all your disputes"
  3,56,"As for those who disbelieve, I will subject them to a severe punishment in this life and the Hereafter, and they will have no helpers"
  3,57,"And as for those who believe and do good, they will be rewarded in full. And Allah does not like the wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  3,58,We recite ňĻallňļ this to you ňĻO Prophetňļ as one of the signs¬†and ňĻasňļ a wise reminder
  3,59,"Indeed, the example of Jesus in the sight of Allah is like that of Adam. He created him from dust, then said to him, ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And he was"
  3,60,"This is the truth from your Lord, so do not be one of those who doubt"
  3,61,"Now, whoever disputes with you ňĻO Prophetňļ concerning Jesus after full knowledge has come to you, say, ‚ÄúCome! Let us gather our children and your children, our women and your women, ourselves and yourselves‚ÄĒthen let us sincerely invoke Allah‚Äôs curse upon the liars.‚ÄĚ"
  3,62,"Certainly, this is the true narrative, and there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Allah. And indeed, Allah ňĻaloneňļ is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,63,"If they turn away, then surely Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of the corruptors"
  3,64,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO People of the Book! Let us come to common terms: that we will worship none but Allah, associate none with Him, nor take one another as lords instead of Allah.‚ÄĚ But if they turn away, then say, ‚ÄúBear witness that we have submitted ňĻto Allah aloneňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  3,65,"O People of the Book! Why do you argue about Abraham, while the Torah and the Gospel were not revealed until long after him? Do you not understand"
  3,66,"Here you are! You disputed about what you have ňĻlittleňļ knowledge of,¬†but why do you now argue about what you have no knowledge of?¬†Allah knows and you do not know"
  3,67,Abraham was neither a Jew nor a Christian; he submitted in all uprightness¬†and was not a polytheist
  3,68,"Indeed, those who have the best claim to Abraham are his followers, this Prophet,¬†and the believers. And Allah is the Guardian of those who believe"
  3,69,"Some of the People of the Book wish to mislead you ňĻbelieversňļ. They mislead none but themselves, yet they fail to perceive it"
  3,70,O People of the Book! Why do you reject the signs of Allah while you bear witness ňĻto their truthňļ
  3,71,O People of the Book! Why do you mix the truth with falsehood and hide the truth knowingly
  3,72,"A group among the People of the Book said ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúBelieve in what has been revealed to the believers in the morning and reject it in the evening, so they may abandon their faith"
  3,73,"And only believe those who follow your religion.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSurely, ňĻthe onlyňļ true guidance is Allah‚Äôs guidance.‚ÄĚ ňĻThey also said,ňļ ‚ÄúDo not believe that someone will receive ňĻrevealedňļ knowledge similar to yours or argue against you before your Lord.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIndeed, all bounty is in the Hands of Allah‚ÄĒHe grants it to whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing.‚ÄĚ"
  3,74,He chooses whoever He wills to receive His mercy. And Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty
  3,75,"There are some among the People of the Book who, if entrusted with a stack of gold, will readily return it. Yet there are others who, if entrusted with a single coin, will not repay it unless you constantly demand it. This is because they say, ‚ÄúWe are not accountable for ňĻexploitingňļ the Gentiles.‚ÄĚ¬†And ňĻsoňļ they attribute lies to Allah knowingly"
  3,76,Absolutely! Those who honour their trusts and shun evil‚ÄĒsurely Allah loves those who are mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  3,77,"Indeed, those who trade Allah‚Äôs covenant and their oaths for a fleeting gain will have no share in the Hereafter. Allah will neither speak to them, nor look at them, nor purify them on the Day of Judgment. And they will suffer a painful punishment"
  3,78,"There are some among them who distort the Book with their tongues to make you think this ňĻdistortionňļ is from the Book‚ÄĒbut it is not what the Book says. They say, ‚ÄúIt is from Allah‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒbut it is not from Allah. And ňĻsoňļ they attribute lies to Allah knowingly"
  3,79,"It is not appropriate for someone who Allah has blessed with the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood to say to people, ‚ÄúWorship me instead of Allah.‚ÄĚ Rather, he would say, ‚ÄúBe devoted to the worship of your Lord ňĻaloneňļ‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒin accordance with what these prophets read in the Scripture and what they taught"
  3,80,And he would never ask you to take angels and prophets as lords. Would he ask you to disbelieve after you have submitted
  3,81,"ňĻRememberňļ when Allah made a covenant with the prophets, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúNow that I have given you the Book and wisdom, if there comes to you a messenger¬†confirming what you have, you must believe in him and support him.‚ÄĚ He added, ‚ÄúDo you affirm this covenant and accept this commitment?‚ÄĚ They said, ‚ÄúYes, we do.‚ÄĚ Allah said, ‚ÄúThen bear witness, and I too am a Witness.‚ÄĚ"
  3,82,"Whoever turns back after this, they will be the rebellious"
  3,83,"Do they desire a way other than Allah‚Äôs‚ÄĒknowing that all those in the heavens and the earth submit to His Will, willingly or unwillingly, and to Him they will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  3,84,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWe believe in Allah and what has been revealed to us and what was revealed to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants; and what was given to Moses, Jesus, and other prophets from their Lord‚ÄĒwe make no distinction between any of them, and to Him we ňĻfullyňļ submit.‚ÄĚ"
  3,85,"Whoever seeks a way other than Islam,¬†it will never be accepted from them, and in the Hereafter they will be among the losers"
  3,86,"How will Allah guide a people who chose to disbelieve after they had believed, acknowledged the Messenger to be true, and received clear proofs? For Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  3,87,"Their reward is that they will be condemned by Allah, the angels, and all of humanity"
  3,88,"They will be in Hell forever. Their punishment will not be lightened, nor will they be delayed ňĻfrom itňļ"
  3,89,"As for those who repent afterwards and mend their ways, then surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  3,90,"Indeed, those who disbelieve after having believed then increase in disbelief, their repentance will never be accepted.¬†It is they who are astray"
  3,91,"Indeed, if each of those who disbelieve then die as disbelievers were to offer a ransom of enough gold to fill the whole world, it would never be accepted from them. It is they who will suffer a painful punishment, and they will have no helpers"
  3,92,You will never achieve righteousness until you donate some of what you cherish. And whatever you give is certainly well known to Allah
  3,93,"All food was lawful for the children of Israel, except what Israel¬†made unlawful for himself before the Torah was revealed.¬†Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúBring the Torah and read it, if your claims are true.‚ÄĚ"
  3,94,"Then whoever still fabricates lies about Allah, they will be the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  3,95,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúAllah has declared the truth. So follow the Way of Abraham, the upright‚ÄĒwho was not a polytheist.‚ÄĚ"
  3,96,Surely the first House ňĻof worshipňļ established for humanity is the one at Bakkah‚ÄĒa blessed sanctuary and a guide for ňĻallňļ people
  3,97,"In it are clear signs and the standing-place of Abraham. Whoever enters it should be safe. Pilgrimage to this House is an obligation by Allah upon whoever is able among the people.¬†And whoever disbelieves, then surely Allah is not in need of ňĻany of Hisňļ creation"
  3,98,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO People of the Book! Why do you deny the revelations of Allah, when Allah is a Witness to what you do?‚ÄĚ"
  3,99,"Say, ‚ÄúO People of the Book! Why do you turn the believers away from the Way of Allah‚ÄĒstriving to make it ňĻappearňļ crooked, while you are witnesses ňĻto its truthňļ? And Allah is never unaware of what you do.‚ÄĚ"
  3,100,"O believers! If you were to yield to a group of those who were given the Scripture, they would turn you back from belief to disbelief"
  3,101,How can you disbelieve when Allah‚Äôs revelations are recited to you and His Messenger is in your midst? Whoever holds firmly to Allah is surely guided to the Straight Path
  3,102,"O believers! Be mindful of Allah in the way He deserves,¬†and do not die except in ňĻa state of fullňļ submission ňĻto Himňļ"
  3,103,"And hold firmly to the rope of Allah¬†and do not be divided. Remember Allah‚Äôs favour upon you when you were enemies, then He united your hearts, so you‚ÄĒby His grace‚ÄĒbecame brothers. And you were at the brink of a fiery pit and He saved you from it. This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, so that you may be ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  3,104,"Let there be a group among you who call ňĻothersňļ to goodness, encourage what is good, and forbid what is evil‚ÄĒit is they who will be successful"
  3,105,And do not be like those who split ňĻinto sectsňļ and differed after clear proofs had come to them. It is they who will suffer a tremendous punishment
  3,106,"On that Day some faces will be bright while others gloomy. To the gloomy-faced it will be said, ‚ÄúDid you disbelieve after having believed? So taste the punishment for your disbelief.‚ÄĚ"
  3,107,"As for the bright-faced, they will be in Allah‚Äôs mercy, where they will remain forever"
  3,108,These are Allah‚Äôs revelations We recite to you ňĻO Prophetňļ in truth. And Allah desires no injustice to ňĻHisňļ creation
  3,109,To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And to Allah ňĻallňļ matters will be returned ňĻfor judgmentňļ
  3,110,"You are the best community ever raised for humanity‚ÄĒyou encourage good, forbid evil, and believe in Allah. Had the People of the Book believed, it would have been better for them. Some of them are faithful, but most are rebellious"
  3,111,"They can never inflict harm on you, except a little annoyance.¬†But if they meet you in battle, they will flee and they will have no helpers"
  3,112,"They will be stricken with disgrace wherever they go, unless they are protected by a covenant with Allah or a treaty with the people. They have invited the displeasure of Allah and have been branded with misery for rejecting Allah‚Äôs revelations and murdering ňĻHisňļ prophets unjustly. This is ňĻa fair rewardňļ for their disobedience and violations"
  3,113,"Yet they are not all alike: there are some among the People of the Book who are upright, who recite Allah‚Äôs revelations throughout the night, prostrating ňĻin prayerňļ"
  3,114,"They believe in Allah and the Last Day, encourage good and forbid evil, and race with one another in doing good. They are ňĻtrulyňļ among the righteous"
  3,115,They will never be denied the reward for any good they have done. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of those mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  3,116,"Indeed, neither the wealth nor children of the disbelievers will be of any benefit to them against Allah. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  3,117,"The good they do in this worldly life is like the harvest of an evil people struck by a bitter wind, destroying it ňĻcompletelyňļ. Allah never wronged them, but they wronged themselves"
  3,118,"O believers! Do not associate closely with others who would not miss a chance to harm you. Their only desire is to see you suffer. Their prejudice has become evident from what they say‚ÄĒand what their hearts hide is far worse. We have made Our revelations clear to you, if only you understood"
  3,119,"Here you are! You love them but they do not love you, and you believe in all Scriptures. When they meet you they say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ But when alone, they bite their fingertips in rage. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻMay youňļ die of your rage!‚ÄĚ Surely Allah knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  3,120,"When you ňĻbelieversňļ are touched with good, they grieve; but when you are afflicted with evil, they rejoice. ňĻYet,ňļ if you are patient and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, their schemes will not harm you in the least. Surely Allah is Fully Aware of what they do"
  3,121,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when you left your home in the early morning to position the believers in the battlefield. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,122,"ňĻRememberňļ when two groups among you ňĻbelieversňļ were about to cower, then Allah reassured them. So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  3,123,"Indeed, Allah made you victorious at Badr when you were ňĻvastlyňļ outnumbered. So be mindful of Allah, perhaps you will be grateful"
  3,124,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when you said to the believers, ‚ÄúIs it not enough that your Lord will send down a reinforcement of three thousand angels for your aid?‚ÄĚ"
  3,125,"Most certainly, if you ňĻbelieversňļ are firm and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ and the enemy launches a sudden attack on you, Allah will reinforce you with five thousand angels designated ňĻfor battleňļ"
  3,126,"Allah ordained this ňĻreinforcementňļ only as good news for you and reassurance for your hearts. And victory comes only from Allah‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise‚ÄĒ"
  3,127,"to destroy a group of the disbelievers and humble the rest, causing them to withdraw in disappointment"
  3,128,"You ňĻO Prophetňļ have no say in the matter.¬†It is up to Allah to turn to them in mercy or punish them, for indeed they are wrongdoers"
  3,129,"To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  3,130,"O believers! Do not consume interest, multiplying it many times over. And be mindful of Allah, so you may prosper"
  3,131,Guard yourselves against the Fire prepared for the disbelievers
  3,132,"Obey Allah and the Messenger, so you may be shown mercy"
  3,133,"And hasten towards forgiveness from your Lord and a Paradise as vast as the heavens and the earth, prepared for those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ"
  3,134,"ňĻThey areňļ those who donate in prosperity and adversity, control their anger, and pardon others. And Allah loves the good-doers"
  3,135,"ňĻThey areňļ those who, upon committing an evil deed or wronging themselves, remember Allah and seek forgiveness and do not knowingly persist in sin‚ÄĒand who forgives sins except Allah"
  3,136,"Their reward is forgiveness from their Lord and Gardens under which rivers flow, staying there forever. How excellent is the reward for those who work ňĻrighteousnessňļ"
  3,137,"Similar situations came to pass before you, so travel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers"
  3,138,This¬†is an insight to humanity‚ÄĒa guide and a lesson to the God-fearing
  3,139,"Do not falter or grieve, for you will have the upper hand, if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  3,140,"If you have suffered injuries ňĻat UŠł•udňļ, they suffered similarly ňĻat Badrňļ. We alternate these days ňĻof victory and defeatňļ among people so that Allah may reveal the ňĻtrueňļ believers, choose martyrs from among you‚ÄĒand Allah does not like the wrongdoers‚ÄĒ"
  3,141,and distinguish the ňĻtrueňļ believers and destroy the disbelievers
  3,142,Do you think you will enter Paradise without Allah proving which of you ňĻtrulyňļ struggled ňĻfor His causeňļ and patiently endured
  3,143,"You certainly wished ňĻfor the opportunityňļ for martyrdom before encountering it, now you have seen it with your own eyes"
  3,144,"MuŠł•ammad is no more than a messenger; other messengers have gone before him. If he were to die or to be killed, would you regress into disbelief? Those who do so will not harm Allah whatsoever. And Allah will reward those who are grateful"
  3,145,"No soul can ever die without Allah‚Äôs Will at the destined time. Those who desire worldly gain, We will let them have it, and those who desire heavenly reward, We will grant it to them. And We will reward those who are grateful"
  3,146,"ňĻImagineňļ how many devotees fought along with their prophets and never faltered despite whatever ňĻlossesňļ they suffered in the cause of Allah, nor did they weaken or give in! Allah loves those who persevere"
  3,147,"And all they said was, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Forgive our sins and excesses, make our steps firm, and grant us victory over the disbelieving people.‚ÄĚ"
  3,148,So Allah gave them the reward of this world and the excellent reward of the Hereafter. For Allah loves the good-doers
  3,149,"O believers! If you yield to the disbelievers, they will drag you back to disbelief‚ÄĒand you will become losers"
  3,150,"But no! Allah is your Guardian, and He is the best Helper"
  3,151,We will cast horror into the hearts of the disbelievers for associating ňĻfalse godsňļ with Allah‚ÄĒa practice He has never authorized. The Fire will be their home‚ÄĒwhat an evil place for the wrongdoers to stay
  3,152,"Indeed, Allah fulfilled His promise to you when you ňĻinitiallyňļ swept them away by His Will, then your courage weakened and you disputed about the command and disobeyed,¬†after Allah had brought victory within your reach. Some of you were after worldly gain while others desired a heavenly reward. He denied you victory over them as a test, yet He has pardoned you. And Allah is Gracious to the believers"
  3,153,"ňĻRememberňļ when you were running far away ňĻin panicňļ‚ÄĒnot looking at anyone‚ÄĒwhile the Messenger was calling to you from behind! So Allah rewarded your disobedience with distress upon distress. Now, do not grieve over the victory you were denied or the injury you suffered. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  3,154,"Then after distress, He sent down serenity in the form of drowsiness overcoming some of you, while others were disturbed by evil thoughts about Allah‚ÄĒthe thoughts of ňĻpre-Islamicňļ ignorance. They ask, ‚ÄúDo we have a say in the matter?‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúAll matters are destined by Allah.‚ÄĚ They conceal in their hearts what they do not reveal to you. They say ňĻto themselvesňļ, ‚ÄúIf we had any say in the matter, none of us would have come to die here.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúEven if you were to remain in your homes, those among you who were destined to be killed would have met the same fate.‚ÄĚ Through this, Allah tests what is within you and purifies what is in your hearts. And Allah knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  3,155,"Indeed, those ňĻbelieversňļ who fled on the day when the two armies met were made to slip by Satan because of their misdeeds. But Allah has pardoned them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  3,156,"O believers! Do not be like the unfaithful¬†who say about their brothers who travel throughout the land or engage in battle, ‚ÄúIf they had stayed with us, they would not have died or been killed.‚ÄĚ Allah makes such thinking a cause of agony in their hearts. It is Allah who gives life and causes death. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  3,157,"Should you be martyred or die in the cause of Allah, then His forgiveness and mercy are far better than whatever ňĻwealthňļ those ňĻwho stay behindňļ accumulate"
  3,158,Whether you die or are martyred‚ÄĒall of you will be gathered before Allah
  3,159,"It is out of Allah‚Äôs mercy that you ňĻO Prophetňļ have been lenient with them. Had you been cruel or hard-hearted, they would have certainly abandoned you. So pardon them, ask Allah‚Äôs forgiveness for them, and consult with them in ňĻconductingňļ matters. Once you make a decision, put your trust in Allah. Surely Allah loves those who trust in Him"
  3,160,"If Allah helps you, none can defeat you. But if He denies you help, then who else can help you? So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  3,161,"It is not appropriate for a prophet to illegally withhold spoils of war. And whoever does so, it will be held against them on the Day of Judgment. Then every soul will be paid in full for what it has done, and none will be wronged"
  3,162,Are those who seek Allah‚Äôs pleasure like those who deserve Allah‚Äôs wrath? Hell is their home. What an evil destination
  3,163,They ňĻeachňļ have varying degrees in the sight of Allah. And Allah is All-Seeing of what they do
  3,164,"Indeed, Allah has done the believers a ňĻgreatňļ favour by raising a messenger from among them‚ÄĒreciting to them His revelations, purifying them, and teaching them the Book and wisdom. For indeed they had previously been clearly astray"
  3,165,"Why is it when you suffered casualties ňĻat UŠł•udňļ‚ÄĒalthough you had made your enemy suffer twice as much ňĻat Badrňļ‚ÄĒyou protested, ‚ÄúHow could this be?‚ÄĚ? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIt is because of your disobedience.‚ÄĚ Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  3,166,"So what you suffered on the day the two armies met was by Allah‚Äôs Will, so that He might distinguish the ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  3,167,"and expose the hypocrites. When it was said to them, ‚ÄúCome fight in the cause of Allah or ňĻat leastňļ defend yourselves,‚ÄĚ they replied, ‚ÄúIf we had known there was fighting, we would have definitely gone with you.‚ÄĚ They were closer to disbelief than to belief on that day‚ÄĒfor saying with their mouths what was not in their hearts. Allah is All-Knowing of what they hide"
  3,168,"Those who sat at home, saying about their brothers, ‚ÄúHad they listened to us, they would not have been killed.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúTry not to die¬†if what you say is true!‚ÄĚ"
  3,169,"Never think of those martyred in the cause of Allah as dead. In fact, they are alive with their Lord, well provided for‚ÄĒ"
  3,170,"rejoicing in Allah‚Äôs bounties and being delighted for those yet to join them. There will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  3,171,"They are joyful for receiving Allah‚Äôs grace and bounty, and that Allah does not deny the reward of the believers"
  3,172,"ňĻAs forňļ those who responded to the call of Allah and His Messenger after their injury,¬†those of them who did good and were mindful ňĻof Allahňļ will have a great reward"
  3,173,"Those who were warned, ‚ÄúYour enemies have mobilized their forces against you, so fear them,‚ÄĚ the warning only made them grow stronger in faith and they replied, ‚ÄúAllah ňĻaloneňļ is sufficient ňĻas an aidňļ for us and ňĻHeňļ is the best Protector.‚ÄĚ"
  3,174,"So they returned with Allah‚Äôs favours and grace, suffering no harm. For they sought to please Allah. And surely Allah is ňĻtheňļ Lord of infinite bounty"
  3,175,"That ňĻwarningňļ was only ňĻfromňļ Satan, trying to prompt you to fear his followers.¬†So do not fear them; fear Me if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  3,176,"ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Do not grieve for those who race to disbelieve‚ÄĒsurely they will not harm Allah in the least. It is Allah‚Äôs Will to disallow them a share in the Hereafter, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  3,177,"Those who trade belief for disbelief will never harm Allah in the least, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  3,178,"Those who disbelieve should not think that living longer is good for them. They are only given more time to increase in sin, and they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  3,179,"Allah would not leave the believers in the condition you were in, until He distinguished the good from the evil ňĻamong youňļ. Nor would Allah ňĻdirectlyňļ reveal to you the unseen,¬†but He chooses whoever He wills as a messenger. So believe in Allah and His messengers. And if you are faithful and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, you will receive a great reward"
  3,180,"And do not let those who ňĻgreedilyňļ withhold Allah‚Äôs bounties think it is good for them‚ÄĒin fact, it is bad for them! They will be leashed ňĻby their necksňļ on the Day of Judgment with whatever ňĻwealthňļ they used to withhold. And Allah is the ňĻsoleňļ inheritor of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  3,181,"Indeed, Allah has heard those ňĻamong the Jewsňļ who said, ‚ÄúAllah is poor; we are rich!‚ÄĚ We have certainly recorded their slurs and their killing of prophets unjustly. Then We will say, ‚ÄúTaste the torment of burning"
  3,182,This is ňĻthe rewardňļ for what your hands have done. And Allah is never unjust to ňĻHisňļ creation.‚ÄĚ
  3,183,"Those ňĻare the same peopleňļ who say, ‚ÄúAllah has commanded us not to believe in any messenger unless he brings us an offering to be consumed by fire ňĻfrom the skyňļ.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúOther prophets did in fact come to you¬†before me with clear proofs and ňĻevenňļ what you demanded‚ÄĒwhy then did you kill them, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  3,184,"If you are rejected by them, so too were messengers before you who came with clear proofs, divine Books, and enlightening Scriptures"
  3,185,"Every soul will taste death. And you will only receive your full reward on the Day of Judgment. Whoever is spared from the Fire and is admitted into Paradise will ňĻindeedňļ triumph, whereas the life of this world is no more than the delusion of enjoyment"
  3,186,"You ňĻbelieversňļ will surely be tested in your wealth and yourselves,¬†and you will certainly hear many hurtful words from those who were given the Scripture before you and ňĻfromňļ the polytheists. But if you are patient and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ‚ÄĒsurely this is a resolve to aspire to"
  3,187,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when Allah took the covenant of those who were given the Scripture to make it known to people and not hide it, yet they cast it behind their backs and traded it for a fleeting gain. What a miserable profit"
  3,188,Do not let those who rejoice in their misdeeds and love to take credit for what they have not done think they will escape torment. They will suffer a painful punishment
  3,189,To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is Most Capable of everything
  3,190,"Indeed, in the creation of the heavens and the earth and the alternation of the day and night there are signs for people of reason"
  3,191,"ňĻThey areňļ those who remember Allah while standing, sitting, and lying on their sides, and reflect on the creation of the heavens and the earth ňĻand prayňļ, ‚ÄúOur Lord! You have not created ňĻall ofňļ this without purpose. Glory be to You! Protect us from the torment of the Fire"
  3,192,"Our Lord! Indeed, those You commit to the Fire will be ňĻcompletelyňļ disgraced! And the wrongdoers will have no helpers"
  3,193,"Our Lord! We have heard the caller¬†to ňĻtrueňļ belief, ňĻproclaiming,ňļ ‚ÄėBelieve in your Lord ňĻaloneňļ,‚Äô so we believed. Our Lord! Forgive our sins, absolve us of our misdeeds, and allow us ňĻeachňļ to die as one of the virtuous"
  3,194,Our Lord! Grant us what You have promised us through Your messengers and do not put us to shame on Judgment Day‚ÄĒfor certainly You never fail in Your promise.‚ÄĚ
  3,195,"So their Lord responded to them: ‚ÄúI will never deny any of you‚ÄĒmale or female‚ÄĒthe reward of your deeds. Both are equal in reward. Those who migrated or were expelled from their homes, and were persecuted for My sake and fought and ňĻsomeňļ were martyred‚ÄĒI will certainly forgive their sins and admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, as a reward from Allah. And with Allah is the finest reward!‚ÄĚ"
  3,196,Do not be deceived by the prosperity of the disbelievers throughout the land
  3,197,It is only a brief enjoyment. Then Hell will be their home‚ÄĒwhat an evil place to rest
  3,198,"But those who are mindful of their Lord will be in Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever‚ÄĒas an accommodation from Allah. And what is with Allah is best for the virtuous"
  3,199,"Indeed, there are some among the People of the Book who truly believe in Allah and what has been revealed to you ňĻbelieversňļ and what was revealed to them. They humble themselves before Allah‚ÄĒnever trading Allah‚Äôs revelations for a fleeting gain. Their reward is with their Lord. Surely Allah is swift in reckoning"
  3,200,"O believers! Patiently endure, persevere, stand on guard,¬†and be mindful of Allah, so you may be successful"
  4,1,"O humanity! Be mindful of your Lord Who created you from a single soul, and from it He created its mate,¬†and through both He spread countless men and women. And be mindful of Allah‚ÄĒin Whose Name you appeal to one another‚ÄĒand ňĻhonourňļ family ties. Surely Allah is ever Watchful over you"
  4,2,"Give orphans their wealth ňĻwhen they reach maturityňļ, and do not exchange your worthless possessions for their valuables, nor cheat them by mixing their wealth with your own. For this would indeed be a great sin"
  4,3,"If you fear you might fail to give orphan women their ňĻdueňļ rights ňĻif you were to marry themňļ, then marry other women of your choice‚ÄĒtwo, three, or four. But if you are afraid you will fail to maintain justice, then ňĻcontent yourselves withňļ one¬†or those ňĻbondwomenňļ in your possession.¬†This way you are less likely to commit injustice"
  4,4,"Give women ňĻyou wedňļ their due dowries graciously. But if they waive some of it willingly, then you may enjoy it freely with a clear conscience"
  4,5,"Do not entrust the incapable ňĻamong your dependantsňļ with your wealth which Allah has made a means of support for you‚ÄĒbut feed and clothe them from it, and speak to them kindly"
  4,6,"Test ňĻthe competence ofňļ the orphans until they reach a marriageable age. Then if you feel they are capable of sound judgment, return their wealth to them. And do not consume it wastefully and hastily before they grow up ňĻto demand itňļ. If the guardian is well-off, they should not take compensation; but if the guardian is poor, let them take a reasonable provision. When you give orphans back their property, call in witnesses. And sufficient is Allah as a ňĻvigilantňļ Reckoner"
  4,7,"For men there is a share in what their parents and close relatives leave, and for women there is a share in what their parents and close relatives leave‚ÄĒwhether it is little or much. ňĻThese areňļ obligatory shares"
  4,8,"If ňĻnon-inheritingňļ relatives, orphans,¬†or the needy are present at the time of distribution, offer them a ňĻsmallňļ provision from it and speak to them kindly"
  4,9,Let the guardians be as concerned ňĻfor the orphansňļ as they would if they were to ňĻdie andňļ leave ňĻtheir ownňļ helpless children behind. So let them be mindful of Allah and speak equitably
  4,10,"Indeed, those who unjustly consume orphans‚Äô wealth ňĻin factňļ consume nothing but fire into their bellies. And they will be burned in a blazing Hell"
  4,11,"Allah commands you regarding your children: the share of the male will be twice that of the female.¬†If you leave only two ňĻor moreňļ females, their share is two-thirds of the estate. But if there is only one female, her share will be one-half. Each parent is entitled to one-sixth if you leave offspring.¬†But if you are childless and your parents are the only heirs, then your mother will receive one-third.¬†But if you leave siblings, then your mother will receive one-sixth‚ÄĒafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts.¬†ňĻBe fair toňļ your parents and children, as you do not ňĻfullyňļ know who is more beneficial to you.¬†ňĻThis isňļ an obligation from Allah. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,12,"You will inherit half of what your wives leave if they are childless. But if they have children, then ňĻyour share isňļ one-fourth of the estate‚ÄĒafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts. And your wives will inherit one-fourth of what you leave if you are childless. But if you have children, then your wives will receive one-eighth of your estate‚ÄĒafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts. And if a man or a woman leaves neither parents nor children but only a brother or a sister ňĻfrom their mother‚Äôs sideňļ, they will each inherit one-sixth, but if they are more than one, they ňĻallňļ will share one-third of the estate‚ÄĒafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts without harm ňĻto the heirsňļ.¬†ňĻThis isňļ a commandment from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  4,13,"These ňĻentitlementsňļ are the limits set by Allah. Whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger will be admitted into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  4,14,"But whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger and exceeds their limits will be cast into Hell, to stay there forever. And they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  4,15,"ňĻAs forňļ those of your women who commit illegal intercourse‚ÄĒcall four witnesses from among yourselves. If they testify, confine the offenders to their homes until they die or Allah ordains a ňĻdifferentňļ way for them"
  4,16,"And the two among you who commit this sin‚ÄĒdiscipline them. If they repent and mend their ways, relieve them. Surely Allah is ever Accepting of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  4,17,"Allah only accepts the repentance of those who commit evil ignorantly ňĻor recklesslyňļ then repent soon after‚ÄĒAllah will pardon them. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,18,"However, repentance is not accepted from those who knowingly persist in sin until they start dying, and then cry, ‚ÄúNow I repent!‚ÄĚ nor those who die as disbelievers. For them We have prepared a painful punishment"
  4,19,"O believers! It is not permissible for you to inherit women against their will¬†or mistreat them to make them return some of the dowry ňĻas a ransom for divorceňļ‚ÄĒunless they are found guilty of adultery.¬†Treat them fairly. If you happen to dislike them, you may hate something which Allah turns into a great blessing"
  4,20,"If you desire to replace a wife with another and you have given the former ňĻevenňļ a stack of gold ňĻas a dowryňļ, do not take any of it back. Would you ňĻstillňļ take it unjustly and very sinfully"
  4,21,And how could you take it back after having enjoyed each other intimately and she has taken from you a firm commitment
  4,22,"Do not marry former wives of your fathers‚ÄĒexcept what was done previously. It was indeed a shameful, despicable, and evil practice"
  4,23,"ňĻAlsoňļ forbidden to you for marriage are your mothers, your daughters, your sisters, your paternal and maternal aunts, your brother‚Äôs daughters, your sister‚Äôs daughters, your foster-mothers, your foster-sisters, your mothers-in-law, your stepdaughters under your guardianship if you have consummated marriage with their mothers‚ÄĒbut if you have not, then you can marry them‚ÄĒnor the wives of your own sons, nor two sisters together at the same time‚ÄĒexcept what was done previously. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,24,"Also ňĻforbidden areňļ married women‚ÄĒexcept ňĻfemaleňļ captives in your possession.¬†This is Allah‚Äôs commandment to you. Lawful to you are all beyond these‚ÄĒas long as you seek them with your wealth in a legal marriage, not in fornication. Give those you have consummated marriage with their due dowries. It is permissible to be mutually gracious regarding the set dowry. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,25,"But if any of you cannot afford to marry a free believing woman, then ňĻlet him marryňļ a believing bondwoman possessed by one of you. Allah knows best ňĻthe state ofňļ your faith ňĻand theirsňļ. You are from one another.¬†So marry them with the permission of their owners,¬†giving them their dowry in fairness, if they are chaste, neither promiscuous nor having secret affairs. If they commit indecency after marriage, they receive half the punishment of free women.¬†This is for those of you who fear falling into sin. But if you are patient, it is better for you. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,26,"It is Allah‚Äôs Will to make things clear to you, guide you to the ňĻnobleňļ ways of those before you, and turn to you in mercy. For Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,27,"And it is Allah‚Äôs Will to turn to you in grace, but those who follow their desires wish to see you deviate entirely ňĻfrom Allah‚Äôs Wayňļ"
  4,28,"And it is Allah‚Äôs Will to lighten your burdens, for humankind was created weak"
  4,29,"O believers! Do not devour one another‚Äôs wealth illegally, but rather trade by mutual consent. And do not kill ňĻeach other orňļ yourselves. Surely Allah is ever Merciful to you"
  4,30,"And whoever does this sinfully and unjustly, We will burn them in the Fire. That is easy for Allah"
  4,31,"If you avoid the major sins forbidden to you, We will absolve you of your ňĻlesserňļ misdeeds and admit you into a place of honour"
  4,32,"And do not crave what Allah has given some of you over others. Men will be rewarded according to their deeds and women ňĻequallyňļ according to theirs. Rather, ask Allah for His bounties. Surely Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  4,33,"And We have appointed heirs to what has been left by parents and next of kin. As for those you have made a pledge to, give them their share.¬†Surely Allah is a Witness over all things"
  4,34,"Men are the caretakers of women, as men have been provisioned by Allah over women and tasked with supporting them financially. And righteous women are devoutly obedient and, when alone, protective of what Allah has entrusted them with.¬†And if you sense ill-conduct from your women, advise them ňĻfirstňļ, ňĻif they persist,ňļ do not share their beds, ňĻbut if they still persist,ňļ then discipline them ňĻgentlyňļ.¬†But if they change their ways, do not be unjust to them. Surely Allah is Most High, All-Great"
  4,35,"If you anticipate a split between them, appoint a mediator from his family and another from hers. If they desire reconciliation, Allah will restore harmony between them. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  4,36,"Worship Allah ňĻaloneňļ and associate none with Him. And be kind to parents, relatives, orphans, the poor, near and distant neighbours, close friends, ňĻneedyňļ travellers, and those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in your possession. Surely Allah does not like whoever is arrogant, boastful‚ÄĒ"
  4,37,"those who are stingy, promote stinginess among people, and withhold Allah‚Äôs bounties. We have prepared for the disbelievers a humiliating punishment"
  4,38,Likewise for those who spend their wealth to show off and do not believe in Allah or the Last Day. And whoever takes Satan as an associate‚ÄĒwhat an evil associate they have
  4,39,What harm could have come to them if they had believed in Allah and the Last Day and donated from what Allah has provided for them? And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of them
  4,40,"Indeed, Allah never wrongs ňĻanyoneňļ‚ÄĒeven by an atom‚Äôs weight.¬†And if it is a good deed, He will multiply it many times over and will give a great reward out of His grace"
  4,41,So how will it be when We bring a witness from every faith-community and bring you ňĻO Prophetňļ as a witness against yours
  4,42,"On that Day, those who denied ňĻAllahňļ and disobeyed the Messenger will wish they were reduced to dust. And they will never be able to hide anything from Allah"
  4,43,"O believers! Do not approach prayer while intoxicated¬†until you are aware of what you say, nor in a state of ňĻfullňļ impurity‚ÄĒunless you merely pass through ňĻthe mosqueňļ‚ÄĒuntil you have bathed. But if you are ill, on a journey, or have relieved yourselves, or been intimate with your wives and cannot find water, then purify yourselves with clean earth, wiping your faces and hands.¬†And Allah is Ever-Pardoning, All-Forgiving"
  4,44,Have you ňĻO Prophetňļ not seen those who were given a portion of the Scriptures yet trade it for misguidance and wish to see you deviate from the ňĻRightňļ Path
  4,45,"Allah knows best who your enemies are! And Allah is sufficient as a Guardian, and He is sufficient as a Helper"
  4,46,"Some Jews take words out of context and say, ‚ÄúWe listen and we disobey,‚ÄĚ ‚ÄúHear! May you never hear,‚ÄĚ and ‚ÄúR√Ę‚Äôina!‚ÄĚ [Herd us!]‚ÄĒplaying with words and discrediting the faith. Had they said ňĻcourteouslyňļ, ‚ÄúWe hear and obey,‚ÄĚ ‚ÄúListen to us,‚ÄĚ and ‚ÄúUnŠļďurna,‚ÄĚ [Tend to us!] it would have been better for them and more proper. Allah has condemned them for their disbelief, so they do not believe except for a few"
  4,47,"O you who were given the Book! Believe in what We have revealed‚ÄĒconfirming your own Scriptures‚ÄĒbefore We wipe out ňĻyourňļ faces, turning them backwards, or We condemn the defiant as We did to the Sabbath-breakers.¬†And Allah‚Äôs command is always executed"
  4,48,"Indeed, Allah does not forgive associating others with Him ňĻin worshipňļ,¬†but forgives anything else of whoever He wills. And whoever associates others with Allah has indeed committed a grave sin"
  4,49,Have you ňĻO Prophetňļ not seen those who ňĻfalselyňļ elevate themselves? It is Allah who elevates whoever He wills. And none will be wronged ňĻeven by the width ofňļ the thread of a date stone
  4,50,See how they fabricate lies against Allah‚ÄĒthis alone is a blatant sin
  4,51,Have you ňĻO Prophetňļ not seen those who were given a portion of the Scriptures yet believe in idols and false gods and reassure the disbelievers¬†that they are better guided than the believers
  4,52,It is they who have been condemned by Allah. And whoever is condemned by Allah will have no helper
  4,53,"Do they have control over shares of the kingdom? If so, they would not have given anyone so much as the speck on a date stone"
  4,54,"Or do they envy the people for Allah‚Äôs bounties? Indeed, We have given the descendants of Abraham the Book and wisdom, along with great authority"
  4,55,Yet some believed in him while others turned away from him.¬†Hell is sufficient as a torment
  4,56,"Surely those who reject Our signs, We will cast them into the Fire. Whenever their skin is burnt completely, We will replace it so they will ňĻconstantlyňļ taste the punishment. Indeed, Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  4,57,"As for those who believe and do good, We will admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. There they will have pure spouses,¬†and We will place them under a vast shade"
  4,58,"Indeed, Allah commands you to return trusts to their rightful owners;¬†and when you judge between people, judge with fairness. What a noble commandment from Allah to you! Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  4,59,"O believers! Obey Allah and obey the Messenger and those in authority among you. Should you disagree on anything, then refer it to Allah and His Messenger, if you ňĻtrulyňļ believe in Allah and the Last Day. This is the best and fairest resolution"
  4,60,"Have you ňĻO Prophetňļ not seen those who claim they believe in what has been revealed to you and what was revealed before you? They seek the judgment of false judges, which they were commanded to reject. And Satan ňĻonlyňļ desires to lead them farther away"
  4,61,"When it is said to them, ‚ÄúCome to Allah‚Äôs revelations and to the Messenger,‚ÄĚ you see the hypocrites turn away from you stubbornly"
  4,62,"How ňĻhorribleňļ will it be if a disaster strikes them because of what their hands have done, then they come to you swearing by Allah, ‚ÄúWe intended nothing but goodwill and reconciliation.‚ÄĚ"
  4,63,"ňĻOnlyňļ Allah knows what is in their hearts. So turn away from them, caution them, and give them advice that will shake their very souls"
  4,64,"We only sent messengers to be obeyed by Allah‚Äôs Will. If only those ňĻhypocritesňļ came to you ňĻO Prophetňļ‚ÄĒafter wronging themselves‚ÄĒseeking Allah‚Äôs forgiveness and the Messenger prayed for their forgiveness, they would have certainly found Allah ever Accepting of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  4,65,"But no! By your Lord, they will never be ňĻtrueňļ believers until they accept you ňĻO Prophetňļ as the judge in their disputes, and find no resistance within themselves against your decision and submit wholeheartedly"
  4,66,"If We had commanded them to sacrifice themselves or abandon their homes, none would have obeyed except for a few. Had they done what they were advised to do,¬†it would have certainly been far better for them and more reassuring"
  4,67,and We would have granted them a great reward by Our grace
  4,68,and guided them to the Straight Path
  4,69,"And whoever obeys Allah and the Messenger will be in the company of those blessed by Allah: the prophets, the people of truth, the martyrs, and the righteous‚ÄĒwhat honourable company"
  4,70,"This is Allah‚Äôs favour, and Allah fully knows ňĻwho deserves itňļ"
  4,71,O believers! Take your precautions and go forth either in groups or together
  4,72,"There will be some among you who will lag behind so that if you face a disaster, they will say, ‚ÄúAllah has blessed us for not being there among them.‚ÄĚ"
  4,73,"But if you return with Allah‚Äôs bounties, they will say‚ÄĒas if there had been no bond between you‚ÄĒ‚ÄúWe wish we had been there with them to share the great gain!‚ÄĚ"
  4,74,Let those who would sacrifice this life for the Hereafter fight in the cause of Allah. And whoever fights in Allah‚Äôs cause‚ÄĒwhether they achieve martyrdom or victory‚ÄĒWe will honour them with a great reward
  4,75,"And what is it with you? You do not fight in the cause of Allah and for oppressed men, women, and children who cry out, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Deliver us from this land of oppressors! Appoint for us a saviour; appoint for us a helper‚ÄĒall by Your grace.‚ÄĚ"
  4,76,"Believers fight for the cause of Allah, whereas disbelievers fight for the cause of the Devil. So fight against Satan‚Äôs ňĻevilňļ forces. Indeed, Satan‚Äôs schemes are ever weak"
  4,77,"Have you ňĻO Prophetňļ not seen those who had been told, ‚ÄúDo not fight! Rather, establish prayer and pay alms-tax.‚ÄĚ? Then once the order came to fight, a group of them feared those ňĻhostileňļ people as Allah should be feared‚ÄĒor even more. They said, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Why have You ordered us to fight? If only You had delayed ňĻthe order forňļ us for a little while!‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúThe enjoyment of this world is so little, whereas the Hereafter is far better for those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ. And none of you will be wronged ňĻeven by the width ofňļ the thread of a date stone"
  4,78,"Wherever you may be, death will overcome you‚ÄĒeven if you were in fortified towers.‚ÄĚ When something good befalls them, they say, ‚ÄúThis is from Allah,‚ÄĚ but when something evil befalls them, they say, ‚ÄúThis is from you.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúBoth have been destined by Allah.‚ÄĚ So what is the matter with these people? They can hardly comprehend anything"
  4,79,Whatever good befalls you is from Allah and whatever evil befalls you is from yourself.¬†We have sent you ňĻO Prophetňļ as a messenger to ňĻallňļ people. And Allah is sufficient as a Witness
  4,80,"Whoever obeys the Messenger has truly obeyed Allah. But whoever turns away, then ňĻknow thatňļ We have not sent you ňĻO Prophetňļ as a keeper over them"
  4,81,"And they say, ‚ÄúWe obey,‚ÄĚ but when they leave you, a group of them would spend the night contradicting what they said. Allah records all their schemes. So turn away from them, and put your trust in Allah. And Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  4,82,"Do they not then reflect on the Quran? Had it been from anyone other than Allah, they would have certainly found in it many inconsistencies"
  4,83,"And when they hear news of security or fear,¬†they publicize it. Had they referred it to the Messenger or their authorities, those with sound judgment among them would have validated it. Had it not been for Allah‚Äôs grace and mercy, you would have followed Satan‚ÄĒexcept for a few"
  4,84,"So fight in the cause of Allah ňĻO Prophetňļ. You are accountable for none but yourself. And motivate the believers ňĻto fightňļ, so perhaps Allah will curb the disbelievers‚Äô might. And Allah is far superior in might and in punishment"
  4,85,"Whoever intercedes for a good cause will have a share in the reward, and whoever intercedes for an evil cause will have a share in the burden. And Allah is Watchful over all things"
  4,86,"And when you are greeted, respond with a better greeting or at least similarly. Surely Allah is a ňĻvigilantňļ Reckoner of all things"
  4,87,"Allah, there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. He will certainly gather ňĻall ofňļ you together on the Day of Judgment‚ÄĒabout which there is no doubt. And whose word is more truthful than Allah‚Äôs"
  4,88,"Why are you ňĻbelieversňļ divided into two groups regarding the hypocrites while Allah allowed them to regress ňĻto disbeliefňļ because of their misdeeds? Do you wish to guide those left by Allah to stray? And whoever Allah leaves to stray, you will never find for them a way"
  4,89,"They wish you would disbelieve as they have disbelieved, so you may all be alike. So do not take them as allies unless they emigrate in the cause of Allah. But if they turn away, then seize them and kill them wherever you find them, and do not take any of them as allies or helpers"
  4,90,"except those who are allies of a people you are bound with in a treaty or those wholeheartedly opposed to fighting either you or their own people. If Allah had willed, He would have empowered them to fight you. So if they refrain from fighting you and offer you peace, then Allah does not permit you to harm them"
  4,91,"You will find others who wish to be safe from you and their own people. Yet they cannot resist the temptation ňĻof disbelief or hostilityňļ. If they do not keep away, offer you peace, or refrain from attacking you, then seize them and kill them wherever you find them. We have given you full permission over such people"
  4,92,"It is not lawful for a believer to kill another except by mistake. And whoever kills a believer unintentionally must free a believing slave and pay blood-money to the victim‚Äôs family‚ÄĒunless they waive it charitably. But if the victim is a believer from a hostile people, then a believing slave must be freed. And if the victim is from a people bound with you in a treaty, then blood-money must be paid to the family along with freeing a believing slave. Those who are unable, let them fast two consecutive months‚ÄĒas a means of repentance to Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,93,"And whoever kills a believer intentionally, their reward will be Hell‚ÄĒwhere they will stay indefinitely.¬†Allah will be displeased with them, condemn them, and will prepare for them a tremendous punishment"
  4,94,"O believers! When you struggle in the cause of Allah, be sure of who you fight. And do not say to those who offer you ňĻgreetings ofňļ peace, ‚ÄúYou are no believer!‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒseeking a fleeting worldly gain.¬†Instead, Allah has infinite bounties ňĻin storeňļ. You were initially like them then Allah blessed you ňĻwith Islamňļ. So be sure! Indeed, Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  4,95,"Those who stay at home‚ÄĒexcept those with valid excuses‚ÄĒare not equal to those who strive in the cause of Allah with their wealth and their lives. Allah has elevated in rank those who strive with their wealth and their lives above those who stay behind ňĻwith valid excusesňļ. Allah has promised each a fine reward, but those who strive will receive a far better reward than others‚ÄĒ"
  4,96,"far superior ranks, forgiveness, and mercy from Him. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,97,"When the angels seize the souls of those who have wronged themselves‚ÄĒscolding them, ‚ÄúWhat do you think you were doing?‚ÄĚ they will reply, ‚ÄúWe were oppressed in the land.‚ÄĚ The angels will respond, ‚ÄúWas Allah‚Äôs earth not spacious enough for you to emigrate?‚ÄĚ It is they who will have Hell as their home‚ÄĒwhat an evil destination"
  4,98,"Except helpless men, women, and children who cannot afford a way out‚ÄĒ"
  4,99,"it is right to hope that Allah will pardon them. For Allah is Ever-Pardoning, All-Forgiving"
  4,100,"Whoever emigrates in the cause of Allah will find many safe havens and bountiful resources throughout the earth. Those who leave their homes and die while emigrating to Allah and His Messenger‚ÄĒtheir reward has already been secured with Allah. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,101,"When you travel through the land, it is permissible for you to shorten the prayer‚ÄĒňĻespeciallyňļ if you fear an attack by the disbelievers. Indeed, the disbelievers are your sworn enemies"
  4,102,"When you ňĻO Prophetňļ are ňĻcampaigningňļ with them and you lead them in prayer, let one group of them pray with you‚ÄĒwhile armed. When they prostrate themselves, let the other group stand guard behind them. Then the group that has not yet prayed will then join you in prayer‚ÄĒand let them be vigilant and armed.¬†The disbelievers would wish to see you neglect your weapons and belongings, so they could launch a sweeping assault on you. But there is no blame if you lay aside your weapons when overcome by heavy rain or illness‚ÄĒbut take precaution. Indeed, Allah has prepared a humiliating punishment for the disbelievers"
  4,103,"When the prayers are over, remember Allah‚ÄĒwhether you are standing, sitting, or lying down. But when you are secure, establish regular prayers. Indeed, performing prayers is a duty on the believers at the appointed times"
  4,104,"Do not falter in pursuit of the enemy‚ÄĒif you are suffering, they too are suffering. But you can hope to receive from Allah what they can never hope for. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,105,"Indeed, We have sent down the Book to you ňĻO Prophetňļ in truth to judge between people by means of what Allah has shown you. So do not be an advocate for the deceitful"
  4,106,"And seek Allah‚Äôs forgiveness‚ÄĒindeed, Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,107,"Do not advocate for those who wrong themselves.¬†Surely Allah does not like those who are deceitful, sinful"
  4,108,"They try to hide ňĻtheir deceptionňļ from people, but they can never hide it from Allah‚ÄĒin Whose presence they plot by night what is displeasing to Him. And Allah is Fully Aware of what they do"
  4,109,"Here you are! You ňĻbelieversňļ are advocating for them in this life, but who will ňĻdare toňļ advocate for them before Allah on the Day of Judgment? Or who will come to their defence"
  4,110,"Whoever commits evil or wrongs themselves then seeks Allah‚Äôs forgiveness will certainly find Allah All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,111,"And whoever commits a sin‚ÄĒit is only to their own loss. Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,112,"And whoever commits an evil or sinful deed then blames it on an innocent person, they will definitely bear the guilt of slander and blatant sin"
  4,113,"Had it not been for Allah‚Äôs grace and mercy, a group of them would have sought to deceive you ňĻO Prophetňļ. Yet they would deceive none but themselves, nor can they harm you in the least. Allah has revealed to you the Book and wisdom and taught you what you never knew. Great ňĻindeedňļ is Allah‚Äôs favour upon you"
  4,114,"There is no good in most of their secret talks‚ÄĒexcept those encouraging charity, kindness, or reconciliation between people. And whoever does this seeking Allah‚Äôs pleasure, We will grant them a great reward"
  4,115,"And whoever defies the Messenger after guidance has become clear to them and follows a path other than that of the believers, We will let them pursue what they have chosen, then burn them in Hell‚ÄĒwhat an evil end"
  4,116,"Surely Allah does not forgive associating ňĻothersňļ with Him ňĻin worshipňļ,¬†but forgives anything else of whoever He wills. Indeed, whoever associates ňĻothersňļ with Allah has clearly gone far astray"
  4,117,"Instead of Allah, they only invoke female gods¬†and they ňĻactuallyňļ invoke none but a rebellious Satan‚ÄĒ"
  4,118,"cursed by Allah‚ÄĒwho said, ‚ÄúI will surely take hold of a certain number of Your servants"
  4,119,"I will certainly mislead them and delude them with empty hopes. Also, I will order them and they will slit the ears of cattle¬†and alter Allah‚Äôs creation.‚ÄĚ And whoever takes Satan as a guardian instead of Allah has certainly suffered a tremendous loss"
  4,120,Satan only makes them ňĻfalseňļ promises and deludes them with ňĻemptyňļ hopes. Truly Satan promises them nothing but delusion
  4,121,"It is they who will have Hell as their home, and they will find no escape from it"
  4,122,"And those who believe and do good, We will soon admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. Allah‚Äôs promise is ňĻalwaysňļ true. And whose word is more truthful than Allah‚Äôs"
  4,123,"ňĻDivine grace isňļ neither by your wishes nor those of the People of the Book! Whoever commits evil will be rewarded accordingly, and they will find no protector or helper besides Allah"
  4,124,But those who do good‚ÄĒwhether male or female‚ÄĒand have faith will enter Paradise and will never be wronged ňĻeven as much asňļ the speck on a date stone
  4,125,"And who is better in faith than those who ňĻfullyňļ submit themselves to Allah, do good, and follow the Way of Abraham, the upright? Allah chose Abraham as a close friend"
  4,126,To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And Allah is Fully Aware of everything
  4,127,"They ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ regarding women. Say, ‚ÄúIt is Allah Who instructs you regarding them. Instruction has ňĻalreadyňļ been revealed in the Book¬†concerning the orphan women you deprive of their due rights¬†but still wish to marry, also helpless children, as well as standing up for orphans‚Äô rights. And whatever good you do is certainly well known to Allah.‚ÄĚ"
  4,128,"If a woman fears indifference or neglect from her husband, there is no blame on either of them if they seek ňĻfairňļ settlement, which is best. Humans are ever inclined to selfishness.¬†But if you are gracious and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, surely Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  4,129,"You will never be able to maintain ňĻemotionalňļ justice between your wives‚ÄĒno matter how keen you are. So do not totally incline towards one leaving the other in suspense.¬†And if you do what is right and are mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,130,"But if they choose to separate, Allah will enrich both of them from His bounties. And Allah is Ever-Bountiful, All-Wise"
  4,131,"To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Indeed, We have commanded those given the Scripture before you, as well as you, to be mindful of Allah. But if you disobey, then ňĻknow thatňļ to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  4,132,To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs
  4,133,"If it is His Will, He can remove you altogether, O humanity, and replace you with others. And Allah is Most Capable to do so"
  4,134,"Whoever desires the reward of this world, then ňĻlet them know thatňļ with Allah are the rewards of this world and the Hereafter. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  4,135,"O believers! Stand firm for justice as witnesses for Allah even if it is against yourselves, your parents, or close relatives. Be they rich or poor, Allah is best to ensure their interests. So do not let your desires cause you to deviate ňĻfrom justiceňļ. If you distort the testimony or refuse to give it, then ňĻknow thatňļ Allah is certainly All-Aware of what you do"
  4,136,"O believers! Have faith in Allah, His Messenger, the Book He has revealed to His Messenger, and the Scriptures He revealed before. Indeed, whoever denies Allah, His angels, His Books, His messengers, and the Last Day has clearly gone far astray"
  4,137,"Indeed, those who believed then disbelieved, then believed and again disbelieved‚ÄĒňĻonlyňļ increasing in disbelief‚ÄĒAllah will neither forgive them nor guide them to the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  4,138,Give good news of a painful punishment to hypocrites
  4,139,who choose disbelievers as allies instead of the believers. Do they seek honour and power through that company? Surely all honour and power belongs to Allah
  4,140,"He has already revealed to you in the Book that when you hear Allah‚Äôs revelations being denied or ridiculed, then do not sit in that company unless they engage in a different topic, or else you will be like them.¬†Surely Allah will gather the hypocrites and disbelievers all together in Hell"
  4,141,"ňĻThe hypocrites areňļ those who wait to see what happens to you. So if Allah grants you victory, they say ňĻto youňļ, ‚ÄúWere we not on your side?‚ÄĚ But if the disbelievers have a share ňĻof victoryňļ, they say ňĻto themňļ, ‚ÄúDid we not have the advantage over you, yet we protected you from the believers?‚ÄĚ Allah will judge between ňĻall ofňļ you on the Day of Judgment. And Allah will never grant the disbelievers a way over the believers"
  4,142,"Surely the hypocrites seek to deceive Allah, but He outwits them. When they stand up for prayer, they do it half-heartedly only to be seen by people‚ÄĒhardly remembering Allah at all"
  4,143,"Torn between belief and disbelief‚ÄĒbelonging neither to these ňĻbelieversňļ nor those ňĻdisbelieversňļ. And whoever Allah leaves to stray, you will never find for them a way"
  4,144,O believers! Do not take disbelievers as allies instead of the believers. Would you like to give Allah solid proof against yourselves
  4,145,Surely the hypocrites will be in the lowest depths of the Fire‚ÄĒand you will never find for them any helper‚ÄĒ
  4,146,"except those who repent, mend their ways, hold fast to Allah, and are sincere in their devotion to Allah; they will be with the believers. And Allah will grant the believers a great reward"
  4,147,"Why should Allah punish you if you are grateful and faithful? Allah is ever Appreciative, All-Knowing"
  4,148,"Allah does not like negative thoughts to be voiced‚ÄĒexcept by those who have been wronged.¬†Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  4,149,"Whether you reveal or conceal a good or pardon an evil‚ÄĒsurely Allah is Ever-Pardoning, Most Capable"
  4,150,"Surely those who deny Allah and His messengers and wish to make a distinction between Allah and His messengers,¬†saying, ‚ÄúWe believe in some and disbelieve in others,‚ÄĚ desiring to forge a compromise"
  4,151,they are indeed the true disbelievers. And We have prepared for the disbelievers a humiliating punishment
  4,152,"As for those who believe in Allah and His messengers‚ÄĒaccepting all; rejecting none‚ÄĒHe will surely give them their rewards. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,153,"The People of the Book demand that you ňĻO Prophetňļ bring down for them a revelation in writing from heaven.¬†They demanded what is even greater than this from Moses, saying, ‚ÄúMake Allah visible to us!‚ÄĚ So a thunderbolt struck them for their wrongdoing. Then they took the calf for worship after receiving clear signs. Still We forgave them for that ňĻafter their repentanceňļ and gave Moses compelling proof"
  4,154,"We raised the Mount over them ňĻas a warningňļ for ňĻbreakingňļ their covenant and said, ‚ÄúEnter the gate ňĻof Jerusalemňļ with humility.‚ÄĚ We also warned them, ‚ÄúDo not break the Sabbath,‚ÄĚ and took from them a firm covenant"
  4,155,"ňĻThey were condemnedňļ for breaking their covenant, rejecting Allah‚Äôs signs, killing the prophets unjustly, and for saying, ‚ÄúOur hearts are unreceptive!‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒit is Allah Who has sealed their hearts for their disbelief, so they do not believe except for a few‚ÄĒ"
  4,156,and for their denial and outrageous accusation against Mary
  4,157,"and for boasting, ‚ÄúWe killed the Messiah, Jesus, son of Mary, the messenger of Allah.‚ÄĚ But they neither killed nor crucified him‚ÄĒit was only made to appear so.¬†Even those who argue for this ňĻcrucifixionňļ are in doubt. They have no knowledge whatsoever‚ÄĒonly making¬†assumptions. They certainly did not kill him"
  4,158,"Rather, Allah raised him up to Himself. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  4,159,Every one of the People of the Book will definitely believe in him before his death.¬†And on the Day of Judgment Jesus will be a witness against them
  4,160,"We forbade the Jews certain foods that had been lawful to them for their wrongdoing, and for hindering many from the Way of Allah"
  4,161,"taking interest despite its prohibition, and consuming people‚Äôs wealth unjustly. We have prepared for the disbelievers among them a painful punishment"
  4,162,"But those of them well-grounded in knowledge, the faithful ňĻwhoňļ believe in what has been revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ and what was revealed before you‚ÄĒňĻespeciallyňļ those who establish prayer‚ÄĒand those who pay alms-tax and believe in Allah and the Last Day, to these ňĻpeopleňļ We will grant a great reward"
  4,163,"Indeed, We have sent revelation to you ňĻO Prophetňļ as We sent revelation to Noah and the prophets after him. We also sent revelation to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants, ňĻas well asňļ Jesus, Job, Jonah, Aaron, and Solomon. And to David We gave the Psalms"
  4,164,There are messengers whose stories We have told you already and others We have not. And to Moses Allah spoke directly
  4,165,"ňĻAll wereňļ messengers delivering good news and warnings so humanity should have no excuse before Allah after ňĻthe coming ofňļ the messengers. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  4,166,"Yet ňĻif you are denied, O Prophet,ňļ Allah bears witness to what He has sent down to you‚ÄĒHe has sent it with His knowledge. The angels too bear witness. And Allah ňĻaloneňļ is sufficient as a Witness"
  4,167,Those who disbelieve and hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of Allah have certainly strayed far away
  4,168,Those who disbelieve and wrong themselves‚ÄĒsurely Allah will neither forgive them nor guide them to any path
  4,169,"except that of Hell, to stay there for ever and ever. And that is easy for Allah"
  4,170,"O humanity! The Messenger has certainly come to you with the truth from your Lord, so believe for your own good. But if you disbelieve, then ňĻknow thatňļ to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,171,"O People of the Book! Do not go to extremes regarding your faith; say nothing about Allah except the truth.¬†The Messiah, Jesus, son of Mary, was no more than a messenger of Allah and the fulfilment of His Word through Mary and a spirit ňĻcreated by a commandňļ from Him.¬†So believe in Allah and His messengers and do not say, ‚ÄúTrinity.‚ÄĚ Stop!‚ÄĒfor your own good. Allah is only One God. Glory be to Him! He is far above having a son! To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  4,172,"The Messiah would never be too proud to be a servant of Allah, nor would the angels nearest to Allah. Those who are too proud and arrogant to worship Him will be brought before Him all together"
  4,173,"As for those who believe and do good, He will reward them in full and increase them out of His grace. But those who are too proud and arrogant, He will subject them to a painful punishment. And besides Allah they will find no protector or helper"
  4,174,O humanity! There has come to you conclusive evidence from your Lord. And We have sent down to you a brilliant light
  4,175,"As for those who believe in Allah and hold fast to Him, He will admit them into His mercy and grace and guide them to Himself through the Straight Path"
  4,176,"They ask you ňĻfor a ruling, O Prophetňļ. Say, ‚ÄúAllah gives you a ruling regarding those who die without children or parents.‚ÄĚ If a man dies childless and leaves behind a sister, she will inherit one-half of his estate, whereas her brother will inherit all of her estate if she dies childless. If this person leaves behind two sisters, they together will inherit two-thirds of the estate. But if the deceased leaves male and female siblings, a male‚Äôs share will be equal to that of two females. Allah makes ňĻthisňļ clear to you so you do not go astray. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"